{"name": "Michael McLean", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Click Energy, I\u2019ve patiently exchanged several emails with you while trying to resolve an issue arising out of a gas leak OUTSIDE of my mothers\u2019 home at a block of units in Bendigo. Mum was away in Melbourne for two weeks, and upon returning home was informed of a gas leak that had since been reported and repaired in her absence. She then received a gas bill which was more than 200% higher than any of her previous bills, but I\u2019m being told that her bill is correct. While acti<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ng on her behalf, I\u2019ve been patient, polite and understanding. Everyone is busy, and it\u2019s sometimes difficult to get to the bottom of issues. Or it needs lots of time. I understand that. But to throw it back onto my mum is not going to work. I won\u2019t accept that, sorry. She is 77 years of age. Her gas bills are so consistent and predictable, and always paid well before the due date. Always. I\u2019m requesting that you look more carefully at her claim because the money is not an issue. I\u2019ll pay it in a heartbeat myself if it\u2019s correct. But the fact is, there was a gas leak outside of her home which was not her fault; was outside of her control, and she was not home to report it. Don\u2019t leave me no option other than engagement of the ombudsman. Please. Thank you.</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 August"}
