{"name": "Kirsten Chirgwin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>So Energy Australia has billed me twice for my energy bill this quarter. Not only have they charged me $600 for two people they have taken the money twice. My partner and I are 23year olds who are renting and now can\u2019t afford food. I AM FURIOUS. I would like to know how this can happen!? Do you have any idea how much money $600 is to a household that is struggling financially!? This should NOT be able to happen <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "10 August"}
{"name": "Mandar Bhale", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia - Get your act together! You are sending me a disconnection notice 15 months after i have moved into the property and have moved my account to AGL. I have been paying my gas bills regularly to AGL since the time i moved in<br> <a class=\"_58cn\" href=\"/hashtag/getyouracttogether?source=feed_text\" data-ft='{\"type\":104,\"tn\":\"*N\"}'><span class=\"_5afx\"><span aria-label=\"hashtag\" class=\"_58cl _5afz\">#</span><span class=\"_58cm\">Getyouracttogether</span></span></a></p>", "timestamp": "10 August"}
{"name": "Renee Haar", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This week I spent 50 minutes on the phone speaking with Ian trying to find an explanation as to why my bill is astronomically higher then all previous bills and feel like we were just going around in circles and getting nowhere. I asked to speak to another operator and was told that they will tell me the same thing and I just didn\u2019t understand .<br> His explanation that my bill was nearly $400 higher then usual was that my refrigerator uses more energy in the winter during the sh<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">oulder time 7am -3pm because it uses more energy to keep cold in the winter . I advised his this doesn\u2019t make any sense and no other appliances are been used at this time so why is the usage so much higher considering we don\u2019t have heating but I do use air conditioner to cool through the summer . Refused to put me onto someone that could provide a valid explanation then threatened that if I get someone to look into it then it will cost me more . I\u2019m a suppose to accept this as a valued customer ? Is this really the best that Energy Australia can do for its customers? Advised that all the information about why my bill might possibly be higher is on the website and it\u2019s a fact , with a bill this high and a total disregard for me as a customer I will be changing provider where I can at least  speak to someone who is willing to assist and is not patronising or uninformed.</span></p>", "timestamp": "10 August"}
{"name": "Michelle Camfield", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>So disappointed with EnergyAustralia. Been a customer for years, but when I call today to discuss a huge bill, they say they can give me a 42% discount, but only on future bills! So that means I\u2019ve been charged and paying 42% more than I needed to for years, just because I didn\u2019t phone to ask? Extremely unethical. I will be changing providers.</p>", "timestamp": "7 August"}
{"name": "Sharon Leanne", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Thank you to Mitchelle on live chat tonight. After 2 calls to try and get my bill that should have been here a month ago, only to be told by them it\u2019s another week away which I was told last week too. Mitchelle got onto the billing team and my bill will be emailed to me In 24 hours. <br> Great service thanks Mitchelle <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f77/1/16/1f44d_1f3fb.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffb</span></span><br> can\u2019t say the same to the phone crew. <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/fbd/1/16/1f62a.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude2a</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "7 August"}
{"name": "John Russo", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I called to signup for gas and electricity.  I was read the whole script and then played the recording which I understand that you have to do.  But what is really annoying is that after I went through that whole process with the gas, I had to do it all again with the electricity.  I had to listen to the same recording and listen to the same script and answer the same questions, even though it was all on the one call.  I tried to tell the operator that it wasn't necessary to repeat everything again, but he insisted that he had to because if he didn't then he would fail his compliance.  I think Energy Australia need to re-evaluate their processes, because all you have managed to do it frustrate and annoy a new customer and I'm now considering exercising my right to cancel within the cooling off period because that's how much it annoyed me.</p>", "timestamp": "6 August"}
