{"name": "Debbie Fyffe", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I was told I would get 30% discount.  So why do they discount 3% on usage, get this figure then 27% on usage, which is less than 30% so that's a lie!, and it is all worked out on the ex gst amount.  Then when it is credited back they include gst on this discount.  Shouldn't the discount be applied to the before tax amount (which it is calculated on) not the including tax amount?  ie:  my discount the 27% part of it is $272 ex gst, however, when they finally list the adjustment on my next bill, it is $271.48 (which includes $24.68 GST)  So really my discount is only $246.80  ? ?????  Energy Aust your bill are so complicated that your staff even cant read them.  I want my full discount of 30% and I want it discounted before the tax is calculated.  I will also be looking at other providers.</p>", "timestamp": "20 July"}
