{"name": "Jamie Naylor", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I'm wondering to who at Energy Australia has decided to cancel supply and usage discounts. Now you are forcing thousands of household's onto just usages discount's that are very poor compared to other company's. Even the letter sent to me, my mother and two of my friends at 4 different households have advised us that you would be putting us on the worst rate ever through you but if we ring we have better rates. I liked you as a company up until now but 4 household now shall b<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">e moving to other company's. Your current trend of sending thousands of letter's out and not having really good rates will show a bad trend in forcing us to move elsewhere and many more. You are just being greedy to still not discount the supply charges as well. Goodbye Energy Australia. Even though it was placed on my file there, I assumed you won't care. so i'm sure stats in time when you lose customer's shall prevail.</span></p>", "timestamp": "5 June"}
{"name": "Umang Parikh", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi EA, I didn't want to raise this issue on Social Media but looks like your Customer Support Staff reads only 1/4 of the original complain (Complain Number 854604). I hope to get lucky on Social Media. So here is the complain again:<br> 1) In December 2017, You promised me 31% Discount on my energy bill but it seems that has been conveniently forgotten until I called last Month &amp; you reinstated it to 32%. Your Customer Service Staff said he cannot retrospectively give me that di<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">scount &amp; someone will call me back about it. Unfortunately I have not received any  calls to retrospectively give me discount. <br> 2) Last year you have been asking me to pay full amount because I am missing the payment deadline. Even though I am setup with Direct Debit, I NOW have enough proof that it is your system which is broken. I recently received a letter to \"Act Now\" as I have missed my payment. This is absolutely a lie because I have set up my direct debit correctly &amp; you failed to debit it on time. So can you please refund me the extra charge for last one year. </span></p>", "timestamp": "3 June"}
