{"name": "Zan Raynor-Gray", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/suzan.raynorgray.9?hc_ref=ARR2NFLpC1XTF-54tWEJej7mWowbyFmx90JgBs89SKG8hd83Qb7JhVYM9P1Aq1lhxOs&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I'm getting really <a class=\"_58cn\" href=\"/hashtag/pleep?source=feed_text\" data-ft='{\"type\":104,\"tn\":\"*N\"}'><span class=\"_5afx\"><span aria-label=\"hashtag\" class=\"_58cl _5afz\">#</span><span class=\"_58cm\">pleep</span></span></a>#ing angry with the runaround and lack of service I am getting from energy australia and ausgrid. Months ago my offpeak1 hotwater failed and Ausgrid kindly bypassed the \"apparently\" unrepairable fuse so that my water would heat until a new metering system was installed. . So now over a month ago Energy Australia installed what they call a SMART meter.. and ever since I have had NO power going to my HWS. I have made numerous phone calls (local &amp; inters<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">tate &amp; the phillipines) and on line chats with people who can't speak english and make textbook answers to questions. Ausgrid sent a technician who apparently is not authorised to work on the 'smart' meter WHICH NEEDS TO BE RECONFIGURED OR REPLACED OR WIRED IN PROPERLY TO HEAT THE WATER!! I have had the heater checked to be sure that the element and the thermostat are both in working order, so I am certain that the problem is with the power supply (ie LACK OF POWER)!! When you phone Energy Aust you never get to speak to anyone... there is just a never ending circle of fruitless options or referral to an unfriendly website or referral back the Ausgrid who are not authorised to work on the new meters. BE WARNED : ENERGY AUSTRALIA IS NO LONGER AUSTRALIAN OWNED AND THERE IS NO AFTERSALES SERVICE! I will be looking for a new retailer and I will be expecting COMPENSATION for all the running around I've had to do for the past month or more just to get my family a hot shower. AM I ANGRY? YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT!</span></p>", "timestamp": "12 May"}
{"name": "Helen Kondos", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia, I am appalled as a loyal customer I have been treated.<br> I have been calling since Thursday as the gas regulator at our property is not working and broken.  Called gas faults that it is an emergency as the weather in Melbourne was going to be the coldest the next couple of days and I have my mother who is elderly and house bound. Since Thursday, we still do not have central gas heating, hot water or being able to cook on the gas stove &amp; oven. I called 6 times <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">yesterday pleading my case and I was given assurance by your company that the distributor company will be coming on Friday.  By 6pm on Friday, I was desperate as I was not getting anywhere with the your company and I called the 24 hour emergency faults. The operator told me that it could take up to 48 hour for them, to be able come to my property to fix the gas regulator. <br> I called again today the 24 hour emergency faults, pleading for someone to come to fix the regulator and that I have an elderly mother.  The person told me that I should take her to the hospital to keep her warm and that they will get to me when they can, as they have numerous emergencies to deal with. I said to the operator and my case is not an emergency?<br> It is now Saturday evening and still no one has appeared to fix the regulator. We still have no central heating, no hot water and not being able to cook as we cannot use the gas stove or oven.</span></p>", "timestamp": "12 May"}
