{"name": "Holly Johnson", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>The most expensive energy company in Australia. With  innefective policies around customers data collection and management and a lack of communication  and transparency, this disgrace of a company would have to be the worst energy provider I have dealt with in decades. Reading all the terrible experiences current and previous customers are having with your company I think all our complaints need to be compiled and sent to the members of the board - maybe then they will care a<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">bout ripping off everyday Australians.<br> Graham Bradley A.M, Chairman.<br> Richard Lancaster, Deputy Chairman (CEO, CLP Group)<br> Catherine Tanna, Managing Director.<br> Ken Dean.<br> Christine O'Reilly.<br> Jane McAloon.<br> Andrew Brandler.<br> Geert Peeters (CFO, CLP Group)</span></p>", "timestamp": "4 May"}
{"name": "Madeleine Barnsley", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>EnergyAustralia, you have let me down once again! How incompetent can you be?? I've just received my latest gas usage bill that was issued a month late, apparently wasnt estimated, &amp; is over $500 more expensive than normal for this time of year. &amp; after yet another 20min call to your customer service line, no one could tell me why.  <br> It's OK for me who actually checks my meter &amp; cross-references it to my bills, but what about everyone else who trusts you &amp; you've been blatently ripping them off?? What a joke!!!</p>", "timestamp": "3 May"}
{"name": "Valerie Martin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi Energy Australia.  Your website needs to be user friendly.  I have just spent over an hour trying to find the appropriate number to.call.  <br> I am having problems with my hot water system.  Had a technician out twice and he advised we need to get our off peak meter checked.  <br> What number do I call to get this done?!</p>", "timestamp": "3 May"}
{"name": "Sally Olivares", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/sally.olivares.1?hc_ref=ARTt10WdWvLcChmE1swQkkmpghfLhSoMC9ONCgPVedThRrTNdNtw4-bfZfH3K-ZDqOI&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>May 2017 we decided to go through another electricity company they were offering a better deal with electricity so we contacted this other company called Lumo.  They told us they would take care of the transfer with them and they would get in touch with your company which in turn you called us offering a greater discount, 42%  because we are your loyal customers.  To my surprise I said 'yes' and then we were told our future bills would have that discount. While on the phone I<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> said why are you offering me this now if i am a long term loyal customer of yours and why don't you offer this all the time and if I am getting this discount so are my pensioner parents, please. No problem to that they said.</span></p>", "timestamp": "2 May"}
