{"name": "Kirsten Supple", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Not happy is an understatement. <br> Shoutout to the incompetent male call centre employee at EnergyAustralia who put the wrong disconnection date, by almost a MONTH, for our electricity account when I clearly requested on the 22nd March that the specific date for the disconnection and final meter read be the 10th April NOT May! On the same day I connected a new property for the 5th April as we were moving and vacating the old property by 10th April!  Lucky I checked my online ac<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">count and saw the old account number was still active, otherwise I would've been left in the dark while whoever lives in the premises enjoys using my electricity for over 3weeks while I'm to believe its well and truly disconnected!! No way am I paying for the full billing cycle when I'm not at fault <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f10/1/16/1f624.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude24</span></span> Then to be told I have to wait 5days from today for EA to get back to me once they find the call request evidence to make sure I did provide the date I've stated...I 100% know I asked for a specific disconnection date as we were vacating the property to start a new life in our new home! Not the type of stress a heavily pregnant woman needs<span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f40/1/16/1f62d.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude2d</span></span></span></p>", "timestamp": "30 April"}
{"name": "Uditha Jayawardhane", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia (EA) must improve service responses. A month ago, I made a complain about a busted electricity meter. <br> Initially EA refused to take my complain saying it is the responsibility of the wholesale provider (Endeavour Energy). After a couple of redirections between the wholesale provider and the retailer, EA took my complain. <br> Then, last week I got an email and a SMS indicating that meter replacement is due on 19th April 2018 between 8 am and 5pm. However, no one turned up for the job. <br> This is so frustrating and a good illustration of poor customer service. Common guys, get this sorted out immediately.</p>", "timestamp": "30 April"}
