{"name": "Julie Favell", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/julie.favell.3?hc_ref=ARThn9OI3_n1gwcTpFKMq2bkluzKb0McMxeQUTDS6pbwSLEBGlTJzK4wAtGApwNgzns&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I say no to the current feasbility study to  burn rubbish on location at Mt Piper Power Station. This area is already overloaded with cumulative impacts millions of tonnes of exposed coal, 20 million tonnes of fly ash in a rural and natural setting. It is the headwaters of a water supply to Sydney. It borders on a high conservation area. The rubbish is not just any rubbish it is non-recyclable plastic, non-recylablewooden products and nonrecyclable cotton and linen prouducts It also is not the method now being followed by Europe. Even thought it has been for 60 years. They are going to a Circular Economy which is to recycle, reuse, refurbish which creates more jobs than burning rubbish.</p>", "timestamp": "26 April"}
{"name": "Meryn Walker", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia you are not doing yourself any favours!!!!!......asked for a final metre read for a premises that were vacated at the end of March...was advised it would be done on the 5th April then rescheduled to 9th, and now been advised it was done on 16th but would have to wait till May for a bill!!!!  Have rung 4 times and get a different story every time!!  And we just want to pay the final account!!!  Appalling behaviour and \"service\".</p>", "timestamp": "25 April"}
{"name": "John Southan", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/John.the.Wrecker?hc_ref=ARSSgFfnvs6jSgqqywkkrXPr2grNAcdHrzB1lMNw9YoBHLvm_ypY7RJPmJPlRDradII&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Everyone be warned the price you are quoted when signing up is not what you get charged as I have found out</p>", "timestamp": "25 April"}
{"name": "Rosemary Sheehan", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/rosemary.sheehan.35?hc_ref=ARQmZq8IJ3dB5D5Dr0gbd9VRfsYe8vbxJZaYBGPm75zr5G_KgwZdJVwJiY1sgPiBYm0&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>We received 3 accounts adding up to $14.000. 00. We are a small household, have  paid all the accounts on time. Without checking our usage history or usual bills you issued these manifestly  excessive bills. They were based on new estimates, based on a wrongly recorded reading by your meter reader. You blamed us because you can\u2018t get access to our meter if we are not home. We asked for our meter to be moved out of our back of house. But you said that wasn\u2019t possible. You won\u2019<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">t provide a day for meter reading so make it impossible to be at home to open the front door. that you think these are acceptable practices highlights the poor opinion you have of your customers. That you think it is acceptable to post out bills totalling $14,000.00 without doing any checking suggests very poor business approach. We don\u2019t want you or your meter reader service managing our gas service. You have have caused us extraordinary distress. Without apology.</span></p>", "timestamp": "23 April"}
{"name": "Timothy John", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I have been with energy Australia now for 4 years. Its never really been a breeze dealing with them but they usually would be ok with little mistake. But the last year has been a nightmare. The way energy australia has treated us is disgusting and they do not care. I had better dealings with them in the first year and it has gone way down hill. I moved out recently (my first home yay!) but they continued to bill me at my old house for nearly two months. After realising this i<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> called up and said what are you doing? they incompetently tried to play the blame game on another operator and pretended like they saved the day when really he just sorted out one of his colleagues issues? After another 4 months we finally thought we paid everything and everything was good until i got returned mail to my new address dated 2, 3,4 months ago still sending bills to the old address even though i have called about sending everything to the new address three times before. I have now gone to the ombudsman for help which i shouldn't have to! One phone call should have fixed this and issue that could have been fixed if someone 4 months ago did their job correctly. Now i am being punished because of their stuff up and they say to me \"we can't help you, we understand we made the mistake but your going to have to pay\". SO you get to admit fault but do nothing about it? what type of customer service is that? Im sorry but your company is pathetic.<br> Sadly this family will be moving to another company if you can't 'help'.<br> Ombudsmen  ref #: 2018/9718</span></p>", "timestamp": "22 April"}
{"name": "Wally Maria", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just wanted to warn everyone about how useless this company is!!! I recieved a powerbill from an old address 11months after I had moved from there. I then went on a payment plan to sort the unexpected bill out and energy australia kept cancelling my payment plan for non payment even though it was  a direct debit every week. I have organised multiple payment plans with them for them to turn around and decide that some weeks they wont take my direct debit and then demand full p<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ayment from me. This has been ongoing for months. I have had rude staff on the phone when I have called to inquire as to why you were not taking payments when organised. The money is always there, then I get ph calls and hassled to pay the full bill. Such a terrible experience I will be taking it all to the ombudsmen. Just wanted to let anyone else know they can be a pain in the behind! Never ever will I recommend them</span></p>", "timestamp": "22 April"}
