{"name": "Uditha Jayawardhane", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia (EA) must improve service responses. A month ago, I made a complain about a busted electricity meter. <br> Initially EA refused to take my complain saying it is the responsibility of the wholesale provider (Endeavour Energy). After a couple of redirections between the wholesale provider and the retailer, EA took my complain. <br> Then, last week I got an email and a SMS indicating that meter replacement is due on 19th April 2018 between 8 am and 5pm. However, no one turned up for the job. <br> This is so frustrating and a good illustration of poor customer service. Common guys, get this sorted out immediately.</p>", "timestamp": "20 April"}
