{"name": "Jason Mills", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/millsy0312?hc_ref=ARTjqsSIf4JODHZJufcIVENdR35Obkgv60pjU2KUAggtdYEbm979JK7FevWSYFe-ACo&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Don\u2019t use energy Australia I was with them for 20 yrs and now that I have switched companies which was done in November they just sent a bill out for $426.75 as an estimated final bill I payed last bill in January so how can this be when I have already had a bill from new company and payed then also they send me a text saying I had an overdue payment on my electricity of $404 in March then send me one again at end of March for $598  please share this around I have been on to ombudsman to get help energy Australia are 5he biggest ripoff companies around</p>", "timestamp": "19 April"}
{"name": "Paddy Scott", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/paddy.scott1?hc_ref=ARQ5dhYS8e8YPUhY1YVz2MyICkFmIsuKLp-vbv7O4u7jg4JmT3-7Pa_FikIqxK1cxDE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>My 11 year old son has received three calls and 2 text messages demanding payment on an overdue $3500 bill! I called you to make sure you removed his number, and you told me you wouldn't. Staggeringly, your genius solution to the issue was that HE should change HIS number so as to not receive any more calls from you! If I was ever thinking of switching to Energy Australia, I certainly never will now.</p>", "timestamp": "18 April"}
