{"name": "Steve Sullivan", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Solar panels were fitted to our house in early January. Agreed to a new power contract with Energy Australia in early February (they took 2 weeks to even bother contacting us after installer notified them of completed installation) Then 10 day contract \u2018cooling off\u2019 period before new solar contract was finally rubber stamped. They quoted \u2018up to\u2019 30 business days before \u2018net\u2019 meter installed - we can\u2019t use the system until meter is installed. Have rung 3 times for updates and <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">spent, on average, 40 minutes \u2018on hold\u2019 before getting through to their installation team. Was told on 19th March that meter would be installed by 6th April. Just rang them again and now told that the service consultant who I spoke to on the 19th March was mistaken about the 6th April deadline and that installation of meter wouldn\u2019t be until 18th April. So we have $12 000 worth of solar panels on the roof and the only ones benefiting are the possums who use them as a slippery slide. Apparently the Complaint Resolution Department will be contacting me within 48 hours. Not holding my breath. Take my advice, if installing Solar, avoid dealing with Energy Australia.</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 April"}
