{"name": "Hung Tu", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi, can someone sort out how you handle debt collections as I have been called multiple times for an account that is not under my name. This has been happening for a number of months now and it's starting to annoy me. I have already confirmed with an EA representative that I have no outstanding debts my old closed account. It seems someone has sent the wrong details to 'Probe Collections' and they are continuing to chase me up for this other stranger's bill. Please cease this immediately.</p>", "timestamp": "29 March"}
{"name": "Mark Cvetkovski", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/charles.pudgington?hc_ref=ARSu1fk3p0-C6egSUukmuCb-HwajHm9duJ-7en_mnNldt8bECz5FtcyF_gxSCwltt1g&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I am being billed for 9 months of my meter being miss read due it being \"obscured\". It has been miss read for 2 years despite it being easily read. I have made a complaint and was told I'd be contacted within 5 business days. That hasn't happened. Since then my meter has been replaced with a smart meter which indicates to me that this is just a charade to squeeze more money out of me. Now I am being threatened with having my hot water cut off because Energy Australia can't do their job properly. Steer clear everyone!</p>", "timestamp": "29 March"}
