{"name": "Jay Tobin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/jay.tobin.98?hc_ref=ARQ2czdcoyRutYA58gzua1JaNjgS9oPx3BG3ert9T5FDrgJV9t01pVgWTqPjcPXzt-Y&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I\u2019m in a 3 bedroom townhouse only 2 of us live here and we got a $950 electricity only bill how do I get a break down as this is shown as higher then 6 person dwelling <br> <span class=\"_39_n profileLink\">Dani Lech</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 March"}
{"name": "Sally Edna", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Here we go AGAIN and AGAIN and AGAIN... this is disgraceful. I have been asking for 5 weeks (by phone, email, facebook, messenger....) for you to do a final meter read, and cut off the power at an office I haven't occupied since January.  Acct #: 4937478727.  What do I have to do? other than pay a HUGE fee for a service I am not using, because you charge a PER DAY rate, so I assume that is what this delay is about.  Surely it can't be PURE incompetence.  Surely this delay has to be about greed.</p>", "timestamp": "14 March"}
{"name": "Cedric Shlosberg", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>In March 2017 Energy Australia made a billing error, by charging me for PureEnergy when it was provided free of charge as part of a promotion.  Energy Australia acknowledged the billing error, and in an email, one of your employees stated \"I have removed the green power for you\". <br> Unfortunately in my most recent bill, PureEnergy has again appeared on my bill, and I have been charged again for something that (1) I did not want and (2) I was told was not part of my account. <br> Could you please help by (1) Removing the PureEnergy charges from my bill and (2) Removing (properly this time) PureEnergy from my account.</p>", "timestamp": "13 March"}
{"name": "Matthew Hender", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Given up waiting on hold to try and sort out the solar situation at our property. Took over a month to mention forms were missing and now another 2 weeks and we still can't confirm all the documents are in order. This is beyond a joke.</p>", "timestamp": "12 March"}
{"name": "Edouard Pour Les Amis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This post to share my frustration. I have had the worst customer experience with energy Australia solar team. I made a huge mistake to trust this company. It is not acceptable and I want to make sure people are cautious when choosing this company.</p>", "timestamp": "12 March"}
