{"name": "Asad Afzal", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/asad.afzal.948?hc_ref=ARQQXd3mt9UmYVvIsb18UTT9AthEB2_QUgGP6xhDNyiVbkg_0vvRW4d4oYkjHKTTBa0&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>im quite pissed with u guys .... a meter reader came to my place in wyoming area central coast , and he left the gate opened , and my bunny escaped , that happened on Tuesday, around 3pm time , iv been looking for my bunny for 3 day and night and cant find her  , why dont u guys train ur meter readers as they just come and go with out asking and dont consider that people might have pets , my kids are as stress as me , i dont have words how to react</p>", "timestamp": "8 March"}
{"name": "Zoe Boardman", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia you should be ashamed of yourselves! We did not even choose you as our energy provider, you just refused to release the billing rights to the gas meter when we moved into the property, then proceeded to send us ridiculous \"estimated\" bills. You were unable to see reason and your operators were rude. It has taken you 6 long months to cooperate with the Energy and Water Ombudsman, in the end all you had to do was send a final bill with credits applied but inste<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ad you threaten us with debt recovery for your extraordinarily high bills, which are no longer relevant might I add. Why is it so difficult to do the right thing? All correspondence received from you has been forwarded to the Ombudsman so they can see how evasive you are being. Send us the bill for the sum agreed with the Ombudsman or I will be seeking legal action against you. Customer service is non-existent with this company.</span></p>", "timestamp": "7 March"}
