{"name": "Ashleigh Ford", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi EnergyAustralia. I\u2019m pretty disappointed. I left my previous address on the 12th of December and you successfully froze my account until I moved into my new place in January. The changeover was made with one simple phone call and I was pretty impressed. My first bill for the new place arrived in January and I think \u201cawesome - I\u2019ll make sure there\u2019s money in the account before the due date because the direct debit has just been transferred to the new address\u201d (that\u2019s what I<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> was told on the phone at the time of the transfer). Imagine my surprise when today (3 days after the bill was due), I still haven\u2019t seen the direct debit come out of my account. I log in online and sure enough \u201cno direct debit is setup\u201d for my account. I\u2019ve now set it up for my future bills but in the meantime you\u2019re going to charge me a fee for paying the existing bill by credit card (which should have been paid in advance via my existing direct debit arrangement). I hope you\u2019ll be crediting my account for the 0.36% fee you\u2019re charging me!</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 February"}
