{"name": "Anny Lee", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>When I initially joined them, they were pretty nice. When my fist bill came, they forgot to apply my solar energy on the bill because they \"forgot\" (first time). They advised to me that they were going to fix this and email it to me. They never did. I recieved a text telling me to pay the bill. I then called them up again to see where my rectified bill was (second time). They said it was coming my way and it will be emailed shortly to me. 1 week passed and I still have not re<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ceived my adjusted bill. I called them up again (third time) to get my adjusted bill. They said they will send it and to check my email. So, I checked but it was the first bill without the solar energy adjusted to it. Then I called them up again (fourth time). I wanted to speak to the Manager directly but they put me through to the solutions department. The man on the other side never once apologised and that he said it was not his responsibility that his colleagues stuffed up. Apparently according to the man on the other line, Energy Australia is not his company (assuming he doesn't represent the company). When I asked to speak to the Manager, he refused to allow me to speak to anyone and I still have not received my bill yet. I am moving to another company and will warn all my families about this. I feel as if I was unable to know why it happened. I'm pretty sure I'll have to call again to fix this! I should have read the Product review before joining you guys!</span></p>", "timestamp": "5 February"}
