{"name": "Bruce Cameron", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia informed me this year i needed an electrician to fix a fault at my property which was unattended at the time..no mention of urgency.When elect arrived 4 days later energy aus had dissconnected power and 2 freezers had thawed.he informed me of this and i arranged for 2 cleaners to attend and clean up and throw food out.At no time was i told energy aus would dissconnect.Not only that they also cancelled my acct.now 2 months later i receive an acct for a truck c<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">all out but i am left with an out of pocket expense of $415.00.I rang energy and after 42 mins told they would look into it.that is after i applied for a new acct.then i received a message to call them.Another hour on phone and receptionist went to ask someone and never came back.then another girl on phone and i had to start again.power was restored 2 months ago when electrical fault fixed but because new acct.they sent someone to house yesterday to connect power..it was already connected and i informed them of that in the first conversation.The damage the electrician fixed was caused by main supply wires corroding and shorting out.Energy Aus were called 10 months earlier re this prob and cut their faulty wires back then reconnected.So not only have i paid for repairs caused by their old wires also out of pocket for goods and clean up.What a pathetic service.appears no one knows whats going on..or can help.</span></p>", "timestamp": "28 September 2017"}
{"name": "Heather Galloway", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I DONT EVEN KNOW WHERE TO START WITH THE ISSUES I HAVE WITH THIS COMPANY! MULTIPLE PHONE CALLS AND ENOUGH PMS SENT TO SAY IVE ALMOST WRITTEN A NOVEL WOULD BE AN UNDERSTATEMENT. YOU ARE THE WORST COMPANY I HAVE EVER HAD TO DEAL WITH IN MY LIFE. AND I SUGGEST TO  ANYBODY THINKING OF SIGNING UP WITH ENERGY AUSTRALIA TO RUN!  DONT DO IT. YOU WILL WASTE MORE TIME AND EFFORT TRYING TO FIX THEIR MISTAKES THAN ITS WORTH. THEY CANNOT SIMPLY ISSUE A CORRECT BILL EVER AND YOU WILL BE BANGING YOUR HEAD AGAINST A BRICK WALL LIKE I HAVE BEEN FOR THE LAST 2 MONTHS. WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE I HAVE EVER EXPERIENCED. AND JUST READING THE OTHER CUSTOMER POSTS ON HERE IM CLEARLY NOT THE ONLY ONE THAT HAS HAD ENOUGH.</p>", "timestamp": "28 September 2017"}
{"name": "Reuben Borthwick", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>After sending me text messages &amp; a lovely letter with my bill apologising for the bill being delivered late (read was done Aug 17th, bill arrived Sept 27th) I now have 2 weeks to pay my bill of $6,230!!!! <br> When calling your company &amp; being put through to the Account Manager to query the financially crippling, domestic use bill, all she could say was \"it was an actual reading, it's correct, you have 2 weeks to pay\"! I understand no-one cares at Energy Australia but six grand i<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">s a huge amount for any family to cough up in a quarter let alone a fortnight.<br> Disgraceful that the options I were given were  to pay another $500 for someone to come out &amp; ascertain why it was so high, or to go to Bunnings &amp; buy a device or get a level 2 electrician to change our entire meter board so we can change to a cheaper plan <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><br> $6,230; you won't be getting it in 2 weeks! And we won't be staying with your company for much longer either.</span></p>", "timestamp": "27 September 2017"}
