{"name": "Darrell Firth", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I want to make a complain about the jump in price this quarter. This is unfair and totally unacceptable for a basic neccesity in a first world country such as Australia. We have been keeping our power bill under the $300 mark and suddenly $550 for this quarter. We realise its winter but we have never used the heater, and i hate to think of what the cost would have been, had we used it. Imagine when it comes summer and a week full of +40oC days hits, is Australia to not use its air conditioner s because no one can afford it. Very unhappy customer!</p>", "timestamp": "20 September 2017"}
{"name": "Karen Lewis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Appalling performance and service. Energy Australia installed a smart net meter in my home months ago after much delay. I started using power as recommended in peak time at higher rate while it is light to maximise my solar saving. I just received my account and no reporting on solar use at all and no buy back either. After spending 3/4 hour on the phone to various people I was informed that there has been no solar generation at my home either because I consumed it all myself<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> (ridiculous statement) or your installer of the meter turned off the inverter and forgot to turn it on again. Further   I have to engage and pay a level 2 electrician to verify/fix you fault installation. Further bad luck to me that for last 3 months I had no solar operating but paid premium rates to you. I think this would make a marvellous story on The Checkout or a Current Affair.</span></p>", "timestamp": "20 September 2017"}
{"name": "Robyn Chapman", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Really disappointed that the second bill I get from you guys, has the same error. How can you get a 5 confused with a 7 and charge me hundreds of dollars extra on a meter reading .....twice ???? I shouldn't have to check my meter everytime you read it to ensure I'm not being overcharged! It's an absolute joke.</p>", "timestamp": "16 September 2017"}
{"name": "Parm Dhindsa", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Building new house...want Gas connection from Energy Australia...apply at least at Frame stage..Lucky if you get connection in 12 weeks....!</p>", "timestamp": "15 September 2017"}
{"name": "Kate Elizabeth", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hey Energy Australia. Just a thought: if another energy company has said I've asked to transfer my account to them, chances are I've asked them to do it. Your set script, telling me that the new company are 'stealing' my account from you is in no way going to make me sympathetic towards you. Instead of claiming your accounts are being stolen, why not look at why someone might want to leave your business. No biggie though. your customer service was atrocious the whole time I was with you, so no reason it would change at the end.</p>", "timestamp": "15 September 2017"}
