{"name": "Robert Obter", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/robbie230272?hc_ref=ARTKqa08DjcjorrZBMRcoWDwYbuC_M7-5LAKvmh7uu2ifEg2A-vVWELKuH4QEld8mqY&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia I am saddened by your response.  For a few quarters I have been receiving ridiculous amounts on my bill which did not compute.  To me, the bill seemed too low to be correct but I kept paying it.  After a while I decided to ask a few people around that I know what their bills were and compared it to mine.  Yes, my bill definitely was not right.  I decided to call EA and told them the concern.  The customer rep lady stated that my bill looked right and there wa<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">s nothing to worry about after I told her my type of usage.  But she said she would talk to the billing department to have a second set of eyes to look at the situation.   I was right, somehow when I moved to a new place when they transferred the energy usage from one place to another they only were charging me supply charges and not service charges.  Their proposition was that they will bill me for the last 9 months being 3 quarters and apply a discount if I paid it on time.   Now in the world of great customer service; if you as the company providing the service made an error on your side; would you not waive any charges for previous bills and start with a clean slate.  Personally I should have gone with another energy company as Energy Australia no longer appeals to me.  I know two people at work who have had similar issues with EA and there will be more complaints to the ombudsman issued shortly.  What happened to the good old days when everything was dealt with in Australia and there were no outsourced customer service operators.</span></p>", "timestamp": "28 August 2017"}
