{"name": "Peter Ling", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/peter.ling?hc_ref=ARTpmHHJQyuvbKKZNfxq0rTly8Bg2x542ogKjQoFAgYt46hGeVr2oCEbGIKqO9Ec8PE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I decided to change from Energy Australia to another Company offering a better deal. Energy Australia then contacted me offering a 32% discount on my Bill when paid on time if I stayed with them. Obviously this sounded like a great deal, so I agreed. After speaking with a friend of mine in the industry, he suggested I check to find out if my KWH cost would remain the same. Lucky I took his advise! KWH charge was put up by from .26 cents to .31 cents. There goes the fantastic <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">discount I thought I was getting. Bloody CROOKS, and I will be referring my matter to the Energy Ombudsman. To add insult when enquiring about this, they kept me on hold for 40 minutes whilst passing me on to different Departments.  In the end I hung up. So be warned everyone, check what cost increases are involved in other areas of your Bill before you accept a so called 'discount' from these Blood Suckers!</span></p>", "timestamp": "11 August 2017"}
{"name": "Karen Anne", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I need to contact you to advise change of details but as no-one at Energy Australia is available at 5.30 I have been told that I have to wait at least 10 minutes. Dinner time?  Should I send morse code?  Please take your time...I like wasting mine.</p>", "timestamp": "11 August 2017"}
