{"name": "Geoff Cook", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I have been with Energy Australia for some time now. I registered with One Big Switch during ghe weekend and I can get 28% off with Alinta Energy. Currently we are on a 24% discount with Energy Australia. I have compared the current pricing schedule between both companies using my most recent account and if I stay with Energy Australia it will be costing me a minimum of $210 more a year, than if I was with Alinta Energy. I have just spent approximately  60 minutes on the phon<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">e to your company to be told you cannot offer me more discount; most of the time I was on hold and finally I asked to speak to a supervisor/manager and was told a number of times these people do not talk to customers. Eventually a supervisor spoke with me, but could not offer me any more discount. I explained that they have now lost a loyal customer and furthermore I will be advising my family members of this better deal at Alinta Energy. My family members had previously signed up with Energy Australia because of our recommendation. One very unhappy customer!</span></p>", "timestamp": "6 August 2017"}
