{"name": "Christopher Ian Wilson", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hey guys, I got my bill directly in NetBank and clicked on the \"Pay Now\" icon. It autopopulates the payment form to pay the full amount on the due date. Lucky I bothered to read the PDF bill and made the amount and schedule adjustments manually! Maybe you want to talk to Commonwealth about this little bit of user-end opacity.</p>", "timestamp": "5 August 2017"}
{"name": "Herman Zirkzee", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/herman.zirkzee?hc_ref=ARQb1KxFfKJt3qWZw6_i3gCAq8iprO9BNjhe-mJ80vUUvx47ojkQ-SPEXbBx3kHBs_g&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I would really appreciate if you would stop sending me ``no-reply`` coward act emails with gobbledygook about so called discounts. Offering discounts is proof that you are overcharging people. We are a pensioner couple looking after my 106 year old mother and desperately try to keep our house warm, or cool in summer, but you guys keep putting up the cost of electricity so that your CEO`s can enjoy their multi million dollar packages. The sooner utilities are put back under govt control the better. Thank you.</p>", "timestamp": "4 August 2017"}
