{"name": "Tom Byers", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just received a phone call from James who had a special offer for me as a \"valued Energy Australia customer\". I'm cynical of such unsolicited approaches, but I gave James the benefit of the doubt. The conversation went like this:<br> James: \"I see that you have electricity connected with us; not sure if you have gas also available at your property?\"<br> Me: \"No, we don't have gas.\"<br> James: \"That's fine. Thanks.\" [Click]<br> Obviously James' time is more valuably spent chasing customers that he can sign up on a gas supply contract. That's fine, I get it. As such I won't be wasting my own valuable time taking ANY phone calls from Energy Australia in future. Please only contact me by email, so I can either divert marketing material to my Junk mailbox or respond to your queries when it is convenient for me.</p>", "timestamp": "20 July 2017"}
