{"name": "Sophie Durham", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>You guys seriously need to review your systems and procedures. Just received a letter to increase my monthly payment by $53 p/m even though my account is over $400 in credit!! Ring to find out why and the guy was useless, just said he could change it for me no explanation as to why it was being increased. I know how to change it in 'My Account' as I regularly monitor our bills and change accordingly when needed. Oh and of cause your website kept bumping me out every time I tr<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ied to get into the regular payment plan to change it!<br> Also not impressed you replaced one of my discount amounts on my bill with a # to hide the fact you reduced my discount by 2%. And there was no reference or explanation anywhere on the bill what the # referred to. At least he managed to get that sorted eventually, although I didn't appreciate that he kept saying he was increasing my discount for me. No dude you were just reinstating what should have been there to begin with! Guess I'll be spending my weekend comparing energy suppliers!</span></p>", "timestamp": "6 July 2017"}
{"name": "Naru Hodo", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I would strongly recommend NOT TO SIGN UP OR TRANSFER to Energy Australia. They have one of the worst services ever!  A welcome package that did not come until problems arise and the response was \"oh we'll backdate it!\" and then they used the wrong NMI number even though earlier on, they were the ones who provided us with the NMI number.  Then that had the gall to say \"We never make mistakes! It's your fault!\" How can it be our fault given that we have lived in the same place for the past few years with the same service provider who had NO ISSUES with our NMI number.  For your own sanity and to protect your wallets, DO NOT SIGN UP WITH ENERGY AUSTRALIA!</p>", "timestamp": "3 July 2017"}
{"name": "Heather Maxwell", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>EnergyAustralia I am extremely unhappy with your service to say the least. After moving into my apartment in December 2016 and then receiving my first bill in the new year, I had to query the service address because it listed me as being at a different address to where I actually lived. After numerous phone calls and being hung up on multiple times, you FINALLY came to the conclusion that I was being billed for a Shop in my building rather than at my Unit residential rate. I <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">then started receiving bills for BOTH the Shop and the Unit. Again, numerous calls to clarify I should only be receiving 1 x bill, you 'cleared it up'. My relief in my belief that this ordeal was finally over and I would simply be able to pay a bill like normal was short lived. I soon received a notice addressed to 'the occupant' in the mail from Ausgrid that if my energy bill was not paid I would have my power turned off. Obviously surprised I phoned EnergyAustralia AGAIN and was reassured all was fine and it must have been delivered to the wrong address. So what happened? My power got switched off. I had been paying my bills against the Shop's meter number after all. That was a month ago, and guess what - we have power - but I am YET AGAIN receiving bills for BOTH addresses. SERIOUSLY what do I have to do to get this fixed? <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/timmy.wenham?fref=mentions\">Timmy Wenham</a> <span class=\"_39_n profileLink\">Linda Danielsson</span> <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/jesse.kooraram?fref=mentions\">Jesse Pepper Kooraram</a> <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span></span></p>", "timestamp": "3 July 2017"}
{"name": "Judith Brading", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Still waiting for your distributor to get back to us and check out the data logger.  This has gone on since 26th June.  One excuse was Ramadan holiday.</p>", "timestamp": "3 July 2017"}
{"name": "Marc F Fleming", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/marc.f.fleming?hc_ref=ARQuA2XDIXXJFjOfKvichz-poXDr2VpiwjLNjKDV2JkW2Spficjn05vYAN8YmhCK998&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Not happy Energy Australia! I have moved from your company having transferred only 7 days ago to my new provider. I haven't yet received a final bill to pay (I'm obviously expecting one) but tonight I get a phone call from one of your customer service operators telling me that I have an overdue bill that I must pay now or risk debt collection. At that stage, I was on hands free in my car - I told him this, yet he wanted me to pay by credit card over the phone, right then and <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">there or else. I reminded him that I; 1. I haven't yet received a bill to pay and 2. moved only 7 days ago and he is threatening debt collection?? that's just ludicrous and 3. I find this extremely rude customer service. For the record, the bill will be paid but your overzealous customer service operators need to pull their heads in! I think I made a good decision going elsewhere for my gas/electric.</span></p>", "timestamp": "3 July 2017"}
