{"name": "Matt Lamont", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Enjoying a lovely candle lit evening thanks to Energy Australia's incompetence. Cheers for having our power wrongfully disconnected guys <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ffc/1/16/1f44d.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\udc4d</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "18 April 2017"}
{"name": "Gillian Reffell", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/gillian.reffell?hc_ref=ARSRGQON9BMMtB5xERGj4tWq-VHKX8gWurt3dV7TjV5poUdVk7PgBrn3w9_zTucQ7WE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I was recently comparing electricity companies because I was concerned about the amount of carbon pollution from making electricity. <br> I found that Energy Australia produces 90% of its energy from fossil fuels. That means only 10% is from renewables. Gawd how pathetic!!<br> I think Australia should be reducing its emissions not increasing them. <br> Energy Australia get out of dirty fossil fuels!! Move decisively to renewables. Please. <br> Handing the next generation a dying planet would<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> be shameful!<br> GET OUT OF FOSSIL FUELS!</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 April 2017"}
