{"name": "Jamie Byrne", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I am very disappointed with Energy Australia.  My account was disconnected (human error) and I was not receiving my bills.  However, I felt I did all I could as a consumer and contacted Energy Australia on several occasions to inquire about my bill, but was told that I was in credit and did not have anything to pay.  After months pass by, I get a letter advising of error and now have a lot of money to pay back.  I trusted Energy Australia for many years and expected they would be professional in terms of their practices.  However, this matter has caused great distress. Not happy Energy Australia and not happy with your lack of communication regarding the matter!!!!</p>", "timestamp": "13 April 2017"}
{"name": "Mon Palmer", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This morning I rang to talk about my account, a very helpful, friendly man named Apurva helped me out and done what he could. He then continued to give me advice on heating and how to try to keep my electricity usage down to a minimum. I think Apurva needs recognition on his excellent customer service, I have never spoken to any representative anywhere as helpful as him!  <br> You will all probably read this and think - yes he was just doing his job - but he really did go out of his way to explain to me about different heating appliances, even where to buy them and health benefits of using certain heaters! He really is an asset to your company, thank you Apurva for your excellent customer service and all your help <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f7f/1/16/1f60a.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude0a</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "12 April 2017"}
{"name": "Damian Daviez", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Maybe you should make sure you maintain customers information correctly. I have spent many an hour over the last couple of months about my concession, one bill it's there the next it's not. It's either your staff or your computers that stuff up. FIX IT!!! You blame DSCI but they have it on their records that you have all the information.</p>", "timestamp": "12 April 2017"}
{"name": "Anna McCrea", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Can someone please let me no how to be removed from your mailing list. Iv never been an energy Australia customer and i still get letter in the mail asking me to switch to you. IM NOT INTRESTED!! i still have a better deal then what you are offering. Thanks</p>", "timestamp": "11 April 2017"}
