{"name": "Richard Rosewall", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just a former customer dropping in to tell you I left because I couldn't stand being with one of Australia's worst polluters a minute longer. You won't get any more money out of me.</p>", "timestamp": "26 March 2017"}
{"name": "Richard Gosztyla", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/richard.gosztyla?hc_ref=ARTT1lHFi47SF8o3hpQI-NAkx_XxHp-v5DQv0aaA-l3B6B3OHXh0nOJwTFlAD73o_X8&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia, how is it, that after cancelling my service with you nearly six months ago that I am now getting a bill for $84.95? I have received no bill on the mail at all, and then I receive a text message from a Collections Company telling me to pay up? And then I'm told that the bill is from 2015. When I call you, no one can tell me about it and that's because I'm constantly cut off whilst someone is transferring my call to another department. The service you provided when I was a customer was substandard and it seems now this continues. I would like someone to contact me about this, preferably someone who knows how to use a phone, so this matter can be rectified before my credit is destroyed by your constant shortcomings</p>", "timestamp": "26 March 2017"}
{"name": "Jordos Misses", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I would like to know if there is an option to have your supply as Off Peak only?  My husband passed last August and upon calling had account changed into my name and was given a new plan.  For the life of me I do not understand how my bill this quarter is only $100 less than last quarter when there is only 1 person in the home and works 5 days a week and with less appliances being operated - this bill is $846! I don't use hot water for washing clothes, a dryer, turn off TV etc at power point when not in use.  I just don't understand.  We had 7 people living here last quarter so I fully expected a much lower bill this time around.  Any ideas please?  I did call but got sick of the waiting in line and received no call backs.</p>", "timestamp": "26 March 2017"}
{"name": "Jodie Ellis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I just wanted to thank Energy Australia for the 5 hour wait today for electricity connection, that did not happen. I also want to thank you for your quick response from your call centre that is only open Monday to Friday, and also appreciate your quick response to the email I have sent. Oh, thats right I havent received a response nor do we have electricity connected. I guess the phone calls yesterday afternoon received from you to confirm I would be home for the 5 hour slot meant nothing as we still do not have any electricity. Not a very happy customer.</p>", "timestamp": "25 March 2017"}
