{"name": "Kristy Maggs", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/kristy.plisowsky?hc_ref=ARRiayVPVSCGPe5UiPR6Ve-uXcHuDqgnUd8NWaxWZiHB9h-mzdWFQa7ZmdlSUpUQH18&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This morning opened my emails to receive a rather large surprise, if you wish to call it that! my electricity bill was much more than usual. Upon phoning Energy Australia I was told that I have been undercharged since starting our service and that they have now backdated this for 9 months and charged us for this! I would like to know how such a large electricity provider could make such a mistake and then think it is ok to charge customers for this. I was told i should have r<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">eceived a letter in regards to this.... Guess what I never did! Then the operator on the phone could not even find that letter!!!!!! She suggested maybe it came via email.... I keep all my correspondence in a folder in my email from Energy Australia.... Nope no letter!!!!! My last bill said I was in credit, i have always paid my bills before the due date... Now all of a sudden I owe some ridiculous amount because of your mistake. <br> Think this is very poor form. No one could give me an answer as to how it has happened. I have been a loyal customer even choosing to stay with Energy Australia when moving.. Think I will be closing that account after this, if this can happen once whats not to stop it happening again.</span></p>", "timestamp": "1 February 2017"}
