{"name": "Keith Buckley", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi energy Australia! I'm just wondering why a third world suburb, like Epping, suffers from regular brown outs lately, specially in the evening. I would've expected the draw on the grid be far greater during the day and there be loads of spare juice in the evenings. <br> It severely concerns me that the Urban Activation project in Epping is planning for an extra 3000 family's in this area yet there are issues supplying power of an evening.<br> Please could you inform me of why these power issues are occuring and how they're being addressed?</p>", "timestamp": "16 January 2017"}
{"name": "John Connors", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I'm writing this out of frustration, since moving into our home about 2.5 years ago we have had to ring up every time to get our bill generated. For the last few months a special team has been monitoring our account and nothing has changed. I got a call from them just before Xmas to say our next bill would be on the 2nd of January and today I had to ring again to get it generated because once again the system didn't do it automatically. I've spent hours on hold trying to get <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">this problem fixed. It shouldn't be this hard to pay our bill! Today I got told it was being escalated again to another department but I don't hold out too much hope of that fixing the problem.</span></p>", "timestamp": "15 January 2017"}
{"name": "Alyson Redding", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/alyson.a.redding?hc_ref=ARQslck2k-f6N4nn5LuolRJvAfc6mNlK5d8lmo2eikcxDI312mh_w7rtCeJLSBl9ams&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi everyone who has a bill with this company make sure you check your bill. For the past nine months they have not been reading my meter and now I will receive a bill for nine months. They state that I have 2 meter which I don't know how as I have one meter with a digital display. Wonder if I will get the discount that I am meant to get if I pay it before the due date. Not happy at all<span class=\"_5mfr\"><span class=\"_6qdm\" style='height: 16px; width: 16px; font-size: 16px; background-image: url(\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\")'>\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr\"><span class=\"_6qdm\" style='height: 16px; width: 16px; font-size: 16px; background-image: url(\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\")'>\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr\"><span class=\"_6qdm\" style='height: 16px; width: 16px; font-size: 16px; background-image: url(\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\")'>\ud83d\ude21</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "15 January 2017"}
