{"name": "Daniel Hammond", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Absolutely disgusted with the way I've been treated by Energy Australia. I made an enquiry with them regarding an astronomical gas bill that I had been charged (over $1900.00 for 1 person in an apartment for the quarter). I was told they would investigate it. Even the consultant said it wasn't right. No worries. Then I keep getting text reminders and phone calls about the bill. After months of waiting, and calling again after hearing nothing (therefore having to explain the w<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">hole situation to a new consultant each time) I got tired of it and spoke to the complaints department. They told me not to worry, they would investigate it. They assured me they would stay in contact, and that it wouldn't go to a debt collector. A few weeks before Christmas, I receive a call from a debt collector regarding the bill. This process has taken over 12 months. <br> You lie to your customers, and you don't follow through with a proper investigation when a complaint is made, so I guess it's the energy ombudsman for me. I have been very fair and patient. I'll never choose Energy Australia again.</span></p>", "timestamp": "10 January 2017"}
{"name": "Sharls Ann", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/people/Sharls-Ann/100011287592502?hc_ref=ARTasTAK5g9hSYzfyy88QHFNSvmWvf0qlXYreTW4H8r7P9HJFJpYq-2FVyCTfpRC7v8&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>The Money Hungry Disgrace<br>  Not only has the power and gas increased constantly, but now there are all these extra money grabbing charges......paper bill, if you want to pay cash etc etc. Energy Aus say the $1-91 charge which they told me when I first rang months ago would not be charged to those who pay fortnightly on the energy Aus card. That was a lie. On calling evil-corp, they say its an Aus post charge.. and try to ram down my throat direct debit. They clearly have heari<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ng problems because I told them repeatedly I AM NOT INTERESTED IN DIRECT DEBIT! The ACCC blurb ab out the 'merchant fee' says it needs to be equivalent to time spent processing a payment, and there has to be a CASH option without charging the extra money grab fee.<br> My issue with energy Aus is 1) they blatantly lied about me not having to pay the charge initially, 2) on calling them, they refuse to accept there are still people who use cash, 3) the 2md person I spoke to sent an email to 'resolutions' department with 'urgent on it.....he did this on Friday 13th Jan in the morning. I told him I won't hp;d my breath waiting for a response, he assured me they would respond. Here we are on Tuesday and still no call back from energy Aus.<br> Like many others I will be looking elsewhere for a provider that can comprehend the meaning of customer service.</span></p>", "timestamp": "9 January 2017"}
