{"name": "Jessie Erin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hello, a few things; <br> 1- do you ever answer the phone? Or could you make your on hold message inclusive of expected time waits... then at least I know how many more minutes of my life I have to waste. <br> 2- I moved out of a residential address and into another. Really simple. I asked you to end both my electricity and gas at one residential and then turn on electricity at my new residential address (no gas required). Congratulations on managing to turn off my electricity as my <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">previous address, however; you forgot to turn off my gas account... how, I don't understand. <br> 3- as I was set up on direct debit I continued paying off the gas as previous address even though I don't live there and ended up in credit (hooray hey?!)<br> 4- I contacted you via email as to not disrupt the phone lines anymore than they seem to be as my request was pretty bloody simple; end my gas account at previous address and transfer the credit to my current electricity account- SUPER SIMPLE, but apparently not. I received an email stating that the final metre read (that should have taken place with the electricity read 3 months ago by the way) would cost me... really?! I emailed back again, not happy as this was NOT my mistake; it was yours. I notified you of my move and tried to do the right thing and was assured by your staff this would be done- also, my old house mate set up accounts for both electricity and gas with you as soon as I cancelled and now there are TWO gas accounts for ONE address, how this happens is yet another mess you've made...- so your lovely sales assistant waived this and assured me that the metre would be read and I would be billed up until the 7th September 2016 (oh yes, all of this was supposed to happen in SEPTEMBER). <br> 5- today... you sent me A PAPER bill to MY old address (again; how you managed that I don't know as I have an account with you for my current address and told you I don't live at the old address and to send things to my new one-lucky my old housemate lives there otherwise I'd be waiting endlessly for a bill that I'd never receive) stating that the $182.97 credit that was on my bill, for an address I haven't been at for over 3 months is now $24. Why? Because you've done a BANG UP job of charging me for the past three months I have not lived there (well done)... so now I've paid a bill that isn't mine and I get nothing back. <br> The instructions I gave were simple, I provided dates of when I moved out- and even set up with you for my new address. And I'm really disappointed in the lacklustre level of service I have received from your end. This issue was simple, should be an easy fix but has been stuffed up again, and now I need to waste more of my time trying to contact you. </span></p>", "timestamp": "6 December 2016"}
