{"name": "Natalie Stanway", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia, I need a phone call before close of business Tuesday. Since early October I have made at least 8 phone calls to you. Initially I wanted to get power connected to my investment property between tenants so I can do some work on the property to get it ready for my new tenant. The first call apparently the operator failed to submit the request. I was told on the second call things were fine only to find out on the third call that as by that time my new tenant ha<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">d also made a request (at my recomendation!), my request could now not be completed and I had to complete the work at my property by throwing an extension lead over the fence and using my neighbour's power. In the meantime I have had the plumber out twice to conduct a safety check and required maintenance on the gas heater (both times when you assure me the power would be connected) and had to send him away each time. And now I have an account set up for the investment property with a connection fee charged to it which I will not be paying. You have given me no power, incurred additional costs to me in relation to the plumber, endangered the lives of my tenants by not facilitating maintenance work on equipment in the house and when I finally got the name and extension of someone who appeared willing and capable of resolving this issue, and rang today to talk to him, I am told I cannot be put through to him and his extension even though he gave to me to use anytime purely due to the fact that he was horrifed and embarrassed by all I have experienced and wanted to ensure I could reach him anytime to get this matter resolved. I will not put my phone number on this post, and I regret having to put this negative feedback in a public forum but I am literally at my wits' end. Please reply ASAP and get my issue resolved!!!</span></p>", "timestamp": "14 November 2016"}
{"name": "Kelly McDermott", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I am currently on hold on and off for the last 20 mins plus sorting out why I have a disconnection notice when no bill received. I am happy to pay but want to ensure I will still get the on time discount! This is ridiculous EA!<br> I am obviously talking with someone O/s!! Not happy<br> I am paying for this phone call! Argh</p>", "timestamp": "13 November 2016"}
