{"name": "Dylan Burton", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just spent over an hour on the phone to your call center to explain that there is a mistake on our bill. The decimal place is clearly in the wrong spot on our mj usage in block 3 if you compare it to the previous two. Note: there was no increase in our gas usage. Your call center staff were so unhelpful. It took me 20 minutes to explain that there was no point in taking a new reading on our meter because we had moved house nearly a month ago and there are new tennants. Nobody is listening to me. There is clearly a mistake</p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Warren Urch", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/warren.urch?hc_ref=ARQ9FtSm5OFwuY3XCO-t-91-MYteroW0q1D4qjESanO-rscJryrWblqqRrFWEH19Bc4&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I thank you for your letter asking me to contact you in the hope of saving money. Unfortunately when I did ring I asked if I could find your rates on line only to be told \" no\" and for some reason the phone person thought they knew me as they kept calling me \"mate\" Not very professional. The process of getting information on pricing out of this person was akin to having a tooth pulled at the dentist . He asked me a question to which I replied \"how would i know\" ,reply was \" it is on your latest bill in front of you\" I didnt have a bill in front of me and it would have been much easier if they had just explained. Thankyou for an unpleasant experience .</p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Greg Rose", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/gregory.rose.77?hc_ref=ARTviGw2sZt9NSIvzky9Xo4OQCSKQY-D_Ix2Aeehe9E7d6tskUXbJHyk7-0M5BWc5A4&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>EnergyAustralia we have just had a power surge in our street in Greta NSW 2334, my question is as a result of this power surge my $2000 tv has blown, the surge protected power board has blown, my $250 airconditioner has blown, the lights in my fridge and freezer has blown and that is what I have found so far.. I know the power surge has affected our whole street as I have spoken to 4 other people in the street and have had similar issues?? What are we suppose to do to recoup??</p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Karen Lewis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>the pathetic service continues-you oblige me to receive my account by email unless I pay you a fee and then you email me my account with a no reply email requiring me put in my post code to view it but the file cannot be opened because it is corrupt-great job</p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Nadia Huppatz", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Let me just start by saying your call centre operators are lucky it's outside of calling times or they would be copping an earful. Not only is my bill the highest it has EVER been which makes me feel sick to my stomach with disbelief ($2400 before discount and that's with 8 solar panels, don't even ask me why they're there as they seem to make no difference), the whole process of moving house stuffed up my original discounted rate because they set it up in my husbands name as<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> a new contract. After being told that they couldn't reissue the previous bill with my discount I reluctantly paid it, was assured the discount had been adjusted for future bills, read my terms and conditions and this bill has arrived still with the lower discounted rate!!! I will be contacting your office next week (working tomorrow so not able to call), to get this sorted out and then I will be looking for another supplier. I know that we're high energy users but my bill has gone up 2.5 times what it used to be! Completely unacceptable! We're expecting our second child in a month or so and I so don't need this stress... <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span></span></p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Rosemary Raw", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>We continue to get incorrect, guesstimate and overcharged bills after complaining to your company.  You have no control over subcontractors who read the meters, your excuse being that they cannot access the property because of gates, dogs or whatever.  In our case that is not true.  We have put a notice in to the ombudsman after dealing with last month's outrageous bill. We were reassured it wouldn't happen again but it has- a $600 bill when it should be around $50.  How many people are getting ripped off, particularly poor old pensioners, most of whom will just accept the bills that are sent to them.  Shame on you, EnergyAustralia!</p>", "timestamp": "20 October 2016"}
{"name": "Lizzie Collis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia - if you don't want us to leave, why not contact us directly rather than sending us a note and ask us to contact you! You always have a massive wait time on your phones - one of the reasons we're leaving - that and unbelievably high bills!  We've already called to discuss them and was offered nothing, so we've found somebody who offers a much better deal.</p>", "timestamp": "19 October 2016"}
