{"name": "Kylie Maree", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/kylie.rix.9?hc_ref=ARSrKGi8qI8Vd1ie8uwBQtWmMFt2q0J0A1cEucIjaHE_CRgWqu245sQF3Jr4fHK_7vY&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>EnergyAustralia, you have just lost a valued customer due to lack of service from your team. We have been with your company for over 5 years and understand mistakes happen however this is beyond a joke. Both our gas and electricity bills were forwarded to our previous mailing address which we have not lived in for over 15 months. We have received every bill to our new address between now and then except for these two. After speaking with three customer service representatives<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> you agreed to give us an extension on the earlybird discount rate given we never received a copy of our original bill due to your error. Now we have received a reminder bill showing the payment is overdue to our correct address advising that the discount is now not applicable. When I have called to query it you will not even speak to me even though I am authorised account holder because apparently you have no record of me. And this is without even mentioning the increase in costs the past twelve months than many other clients have mentioned on your page.</span></p>", "timestamp": "29 September 2016"}
