{"name": "Vince Carty", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Avoid Energy Australia. Their \"Pay on Time Discount\" is a SCAM.<br> Pay bills via direct debit and receive a discount from your bill.<br> LIES..... Energy Australia will then SEPARATELY BILL for the discounted amount and when queried REFUSE to reply to your emails. Looks like a job for the Ombudsman.<br> Their website contact states \"We will contact you with 1 day\" then after filling in the details you receive a popup message advising contact within 5 days. What a scam .... just to ensur<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">e that you pay the discount that you were supposed to receive by paying on time and not bother to followup.<br> So far 2 emails have been IGNORED so unless this issue is resolved by COB Friday I will followup with a formal complaint to the Ombudsman.<br> Currently looking at other Electricity suppliers (I mean Billers) to see what is worth switching to.<br> Lift your game and stop ripping off customers or LOSE THEM!!!!!</span></p>", "timestamp": "8 September 2016"}
{"name": "Sharyn McGuinness", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/sharyn.mcguinness.1?hc_ref=ARSQkueFOrHennEoqWeSDsZvDYvLaMjK32QKlc3bHZblXqAgkB3yWz_er63jRR-6wNY&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I received an offer for two free movie tickets recently and I tried many times to get on to the website quoted, but it didn't exist. I thought it may have been a scam. I have tried again it still does not exist. I noticed that someone had contacted you directly and that you suggested another website. I did get through eventually on that site today but it now said that the offer had expired!!!   I don't think that your free offer was a very good publicity offer and that maybe a correction advice should have been sent to customers who received the initial \"Thank you, Two free movie tickets etc\".</p>", "timestamp": "5 September 2016"}
