{"name": "Melanie Sobol", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Today I contacted your account enquiries line to enquire as to why our latest gas account is more than double the amount it was this time last year. I spoke to Andrew, one you of your customer service representatives who explained that our previous gas accounts have been charged at estimated usage only and that an actual meter reading was done in relation to our most recent account which showed we have used more gas than what was estimated over the last year or so.  My questi<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">on to that was why should we now have to pay such a large amount (over a thousand dollars!!) because your estimates weren't done accurately? Andrew offered solutions which included an extension of due date and payment plans but that doesn't solve my issue does it?! So then I asked what the dispute process would be and Andrew just told me that there was nothing to dispute so I can either go on a payment plan or have the due date extended.  As you can imagine, this is not the way a customer who always pays their bills on time expects to be treated. I am hoping to speak with someone who has a higher level of customer service and understanding of the issue at hand.  If this fails, I will make a complaint to the ombudsman.  Thank you.</span></p>", "timestamp": "5 September 2016"}
