{"name": "Brett Peebles", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Apparently I'm a customer of yours for my new house even though I had to take you to the ombudsman twice over errors in your accounts system. <br> I have received an sms saying that you will be switching the electricity over this week to you despite no one requesting this. When I lodged a complaint online the response today was that you would not cancel it as the quote had not been cancelled in the appropriate time.  What quote? Who authorised you to quote on my house? I want this sorted out or I'm going back to the ombudsman AGAIN!<br> I also apparently have a gas bill in our name for $350 for 28 days of gas.  Please for the love of God sort your billing software out, take me off your records and stop causing me such stress! I'm not nor will ever be a customer of yours ever again!</p>", "timestamp": "30 August 2016"}
{"name": "Chloe Louise", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi EnergyAustralia,<br> I called your Home Services department on Friday the 19th August, I spoke to Dileepan and was quoted for 2 split systems to be installed at my new property. We went through the quote process and I was told I would have to either pay in full or pay a deposit before an appointment could be booked for a technician to come out and install the systems. <br> I happily paid the deposit. I wasn't willing to pay in full given I hadn't yet received the goods. Luckily I <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">didn't!<br> I was told that day that someone would be in contact with me within one week to organise instalation.<br> Well that was Friday the 26th. I am still yet to hear from anyone.<br> I called Home Services again yesterday morning, I spoke to Constantino this time. I advised him of the situation and he seemed shocked that this had happened. He apologised and told me he couldn't see any reason as to why I have not yet received a call. He assured me that he had escalated my concern and I would be receiving a call shortly. He asked when I would like the appointment for.. I told him this week. <br> The tonw in his response made it sound like that's probably not going to happen.<br> He advised I would receive a call shortly to organise an appointment for this week however I wasn't convinced, but I thought I would give him the benefit of the doubt.<br> Given I called early morning yesterday, almost 2 days have passed and still no phone call.<br> I did advise Constantino that i require an appointment this week as shortly I will not be available to be at the property when the technician comes to install. This would mean it cannot be complete and I will have to cancel the quote and be refunded the deposit and you would lose the $3500 sale.<br> I do have other options, but at this point I really don't have the time to go elsewhere, however if this cannot be resolved ASAP, I will have no choice.<br> Last time I organised a split system, the appointment was booked that day. I'm assuming this process haa changed. As for some reason your staff are unable to organise appointments themselves and it seems like it's palmed off to someone external? Direct communication between the two would have been a less painful process for both the customer and your business.<br> Can someone please contact me to book this by close of business tomorrow? I require an appointment within a week at the latest. <br> Thank you.</span></p>", "timestamp": "30 August 2016"}
