{"name": "Rennae Smith", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just wondering why my hot water service recently seems to be entering the off peak heating pattern at 4.30pmAEST during the week. I am aware that during the weekend there is no off peak timing and my water service heats at varying time throughout the day. I have a Watson Metre that enables me to see my energy consumption throughout the day. Up until yesterday (23rd August) my hot water system was only entering warming up overnight, which was fine with us. The last 2 days, come 4.30pm, my metre skyrockets when the hot water system begins to enter the warming stage. Have I missed something in regards to Off Peak times?</p>", "timestamp": "24 August 2016"}
