{"name": "Wayne Justin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>NOT HAPPY.<br> Received my Bill in July and noted that I had been charged as a business customer. Call to your customer line and they indicated that I had been charged as a business for the last 12 months and that they would rectify the account and to not pay the bill until the account was recalculated. Was signed up as a residential customer on the same call and imagine my surprise today when I find out that I owe more even though credits had been processed.<br> Spoke to a customer <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">relations staff member today who confirmed that the business rate SHOULD be less than the residential rat but due to the plan in my case, I am now being charged more because the plan I am now on is not as good as the business plan I was on.<br> When I asked, was told that because I brought it to the company's attention that there was an incorrect plan, you are obliged to change it.<br> In short, because I was being honest and bringing the error to you, I am rewarded with additional charges.<br> When I mentioned that I would be looking for a better service provider who listened to their customers, I was effectively told that my business wasn't important to Energy Australia.<br> Not really what I expected from such a customer focussed company.</span></p>", "timestamp": "12 August 2016"}
