{"name": "James Dumas", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Terrible customer service. We have received estimated gas bills for the last two quarters, presumably because your distributor is to lazy to read the meter. It is at the front of the property, there are no animals or obstacles in the way. Blind Freddy could see it and Blind Freddy is blind! We have a housemate who is soon to move out and we would like to settle what presumably will be a large bill with him before he departs! I received a call this Tuesday gone from 'Hayley' i<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">n Melbourne, who left a voicemail, asking me to call back a 13 number for further updates. I did that which connects you offshore where you have to beg and plead with 'gatekeepers' to be transferred to someone onshore. I have since spoken to a supervisor 'Jane' who promised a call back from the elusive 'Hayley' which, wait, you guessed it, didn't happen. I then spoke with 'Gokam' who again promised a call back from the elusive 'Hayley' which, you guessed right again, didn't happen. Whoever 'Hayley' is, she needs some serious lessons in how to deal with customers and doesn't deserve to be functioning in a case manager role if she can't be bothered to pick up the phone and make a call. My housemates and I are all teachers, we cannot pick up the phone during class and have asked for callbacks after 3:30pm. Not very hard guys! At the very least, I am expecting a substantial credit on this bill for the 3 hours of my time I have spent contacting you to get you to bill me so that I can pay you money!</span></p>", "timestamp": "5 August 2016"}
{"name": "Margaret Weller", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Dear Energy Australia, on the 8th July we set up our account with you for electricity and gas prior to moving into our rental property on the 15th. Little did we know that the account would take almost a month to set up at your end as we arrived home on Tuesday, 2nd August to find that our gas was cut off. We promptly phoned your after hours people on Tuesday evening to advise that our gas supply was cut off by Origin due to the previous tenants not paying their bill. Well ap<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">parently we now have to suffer having no hot water all week because of this. Many phone calls later which add up to two and a quarter hours over four days, we still have no gas and no hot water. We were  told this evening that Jemena only received the work order today...four days later to reconnect. This is now going to take another 48 business hours to be actioned which brings us to a full week without hot water. Your after hours people in the Philippines are unhelpful, rude and have no concept of the situation.  This is so unacceptable and unprofessional to the point of changing providers could be necessary. We would appreciate your immediate action on this.</span></p>", "timestamp": "5 August 2016"}
{"name": "Rahul Garg", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/rahul.garg.589?hc_ref=ARTCFUkLW-A6Z5Mu69Ft9jSGDaQK4sHnOzuHjcW2ORWxvp07WoTSxQ6Rc1r7rrgimjs&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I just signed into my account today and noticed you will start charging a credit card fees beginning November. Raising the rates and delivery charges (all or most companies did it, so why should you stay back, right?) wasn't sufficient so now you bring in this too. It's time for me to start looking elsewhere. Can you please tell me if you charge any money for a final meter read (I have both electricity and gas with you)?</p>", "timestamp": "4 August 2016"}
{"name": "Kimberly Anne Wood", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>It's odd for me to WANT a bill, or two but honestly this is getting ridiculous now. I moved house on the 8th of July, final readings and disconnection of gas and electricity were booked for the 11th of July(a Monday) with a disconnection fee included, the bills due 10 business days after the 11th. Well, I called a few days ago and apparently the bills had not been processed yet. So, I expected to receive said bills in a few working days - nope, nothing. I am now concerned abo<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ut receiving correct charges and the disconnection times as another family moved into the house I moved out of instantly and may have added to the bills if it was not disconnected when I booked it to be done. <br> I can supply my reference number and past address (along with personal details) to help this process of confirmation and billing, for someone who lives week to week and has to stick to a strict budget this has been a major inconvenience as I'm sure you would understand.</span></p>", "timestamp": "2 August 2016"}
{"name": "Shari Leigh", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>so I got my first power bill in about 4 years (no longer a solar home owner...now a renter) from EnergyAustralia. Invoice says issued on 8/7/16, I received it in the mailbox 12/7/16 and was given the opportunity to save $30 if I had it paid by 27/7 - 15 days later. During that time, I received two emails from EA, extolling the benefits of paying my bill online and encouraging me to get a wriggle on with payment. Didn't have the funds to pay it by that date, and was pretty surprised to receive a text on 28/7 saying I was late with the payment and the extra $30 had been added back in and full payment was OVERDUE immediately, 16 days after being issued with the bill. Is this standard? Is EA so strapped for cash they need to treat their customers like this?</p>", "timestamp": "1 August 2016"}
{"name": "Paul Smith", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I have just been dealing with your call centre which I believe is located in Melbourne. I have bad hearing which makes people with accents difficult for me to understand over the phone yet when I advised the person of this they didn't seem to be able to connect me with someone who spoke with an Australian accent. Is it possible for people with hearing issues to be transferred to someone with an Australian accent? I hate asking because I know how it sounds but it would make life a hell of a lot easier. Thanks.</p>", "timestamp": "1 August 2016"}
{"name": "Alyson Peel", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/alyson.peel?hc_ref=ARQ92BdArNOdZVbCVGTush-x6IiaCAT21NFM1TLuxY7d0dpaTMuGTILdKsRoI50Zryw&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I have to get this off my chest I can not sleep - Why is it these big companies give new small businesses such a hard time when they first stay and then have the audacity to make it even harder !! Not only could they find no meter attached to our shops address when we first started but neither could the real estate agent so they said oh there must not be one ! Guess what 3 months later we get a huge bill agree on an amount after they reckon they checked the meter they suddenl<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">y found in the shop next door <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/fd3/1/16/2639.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\u2639\ufe0f</span></span> We start paying it off doing the right thing !! Now just got next bill with letter attached stating sorry we have under charged you so they add an extra $800 to first bill up the rates to maximum on the next bill now a new little takeaway shop who cooks with gas not electricity has s $3400 bill ! Disgraceful Energy Australia ! This is why they get the image the receive in the media because they deserve it ! Not only should they have sent someone out to check again like we requested but should not change an already agreed upon amount - I now request you drop these rates by 30% as we have had another supplier offer straight this rate what do you think you are going to achieve Energy Aust by doing this to a new small business in a small suburb you have now jeopardized a business the local love ! We can not pay this bill at this amount and therefore we can not change providers we are stuck thank you for all your help Energy Aust !</span></p>", "timestamp": "1 August 2016"}
{"name": "Mick Flynn", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/mick.flynn.4U2C?hc_ref=ARTp7_ClaxN2oYvz1O0uCZRqsjcZiTmeLkJKli-sPEFEFzBpG19qu-w8H0gqBKmP9RI&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>After waiting four years to have my solar PV System registered with Energy australia, they finaly sent a text today to say \"I should call them\", my system is ready to connect.<br> When I called not only did they say that they could not generate a work order, but they no don't even have my address correct.<br> What a pack of lazy mungrals.</p>", "timestamp": "1 August 2016"}
