{"name": "Daniel Ord", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/daniel.ord.50?hc_ref=ARTNosHjqkigl81oKQIv80j0GeogikUhdLmNLMNjVcTolICR6v-W2OJBg5a0Oql-TK0&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I received a gas bill from Energy Australia today of $1,336.67 they claim they have undercharged me from the 8th December 2015. I do not think it is fair that I should pay for an error made by Energy Australia, an error they have advised me in writing. The bill even states the bill is an estimate. Energy Australia refuse to waive this charge. This is not the first time this has happened to me. I am asking for Energy Australia\u2019s consideration in this matter and an opportunity for them to rectify their mistake as a long standing customer, in good faith.</p>", "timestamp": "26 July 2016"}
{"name": "Daniel Ord", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/daniel.ord.50?hc_ref=ARTbQbqoNOJOk-du2GTir_kAMbOFHintzqg45kC_fwb7ze2GgEiUrvC8CecnnhwcYWM&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia sent me a bill of $1336.67 gas bill they claim to have undercharged me from a period that backdates to before decmeber 2015 last year. they continue to advise they can't do anything for a long standing customer and by their own internal regulation they can backdate bills up to a period of 9 months. I do not think it is fair for me to pay for an error Energy Australia admits to me in writing they have made.</p>", "timestamp": "26 July 2016"}
{"name": "Angela La", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Thanks Energy australia - I called you today to let you know my father had passed away, and that i needed to cancel the electricity to the property/ account. Your operator whilst polite had to make sure they informed me of a call out fee for the final meter reading. <br> Not to mention the account it about $200.00 in credit. As if calling all the other utilities and companies isnt hard enough , without  it being repetitively mentioned that they had to charge a call out fee , and ensure they had a forwarding address to send the charges to. SHAME ON YOU!</p>", "timestamp": "26 July 2016"}
{"name": "Mitchel Clarke", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just wondering when it became policy for your call centre staff to request customers to check their meter numbers for them. To me this seems a pretty unsafe practice considering the potential for either electric shock if a meter box / board is faulty or the serious to fatal health consequences risked by customers if they are exposed to asbestos fibres from older meter boards in the process of completing these checks?</p>", "timestamp": "26 July 2016"}
{"name": "Jarrad Swilks", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/jarrad.swilks?hc_ref=ARSdkVRPfIbUftl5FgPxolkQzFIrMIzkIOq-LqRYD6_zu2Ie0YA8ho47Dp35mt1PNJQ&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I would NOT recommend energy Australia to anyone... Having just moved into our house we received an $800 gas bill for 2 months... I queried them about the possibility of a gas leak and was told that we probably just needed our appliances serviced and that there was nothing they could do to help us... I was also told the previous occupier had a bill that was $1,600 which to me indicates they were well aware something wasn't quite right with the property! As a company that spec<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ialises in supplying gas I would have thought they would be able to see that a 4 bedroom home with ducted heating, 1 gas cooktop and 1 gas hot water service (which services 1 bathroom only) should not be using such high amounts of gas... We only have our ducted heater on 20deg during the day and 15deg over night... So having just spent $4,500 to get all the gas pipes re-don we thought that Energy Australia would help us out... But clearly they don't care about retaining customers... So if anyone is considering moving over to Energy Australia I SUGGEST LOOKING SOMEWHERE ELSE!!!! Worst customer service!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!</span></p>", "timestamp": "24 July 2016"}
