{"name": "Ailsa Cameron", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Worst customer service company anywhere in the world. After having been a customer for decades with a family, I downsized, one person in the property, Energy Australia just kept charging for 3.5 persons in the property. Never attended any of the questions, complaints around this overcharging, which frankly, let us call it what it is in an inequitable power relationship - theft. Then Energy Australia changed the billing system which caused internally and externally mass confus<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ion and angst, another nightmare - I'd ALWAYS been in credit - suddenly, accounts are impossible to track - top move Energy Australia.18 months of hell attempting to get the overcharging looked at, many promises, zero action or follow up, me always starting from the beginning and never getting anywhere in a bureaucrat system not designed to manage the customer journey. My next move - Cancel the account - date for cessation of service Jan 15 2016. You would imagine that is that. NO. 6 more months of bills, harassment; no accountability from Energy Australia, hollow apologies, no one picking up the mess and fixing it - moral in the company must be flagging on the ground like a camel that has walked through the Sahara without finding the oasis and the tongue is out seeking some kind of relief - keep looking. Today - I've been pushed over the edge - yet another overdue text notice - no bill of course - just straight to the harassment point. I have just spent yet another hour on the phone to three customer service people at Energy Australia - each one handballing the issue to the next, with finally Anna stating she is handballing to yet another group who will call me within 72 hours.........................................Energy Australia. Ombudsman and investigative news reporter in your future.</span></p>", "timestamp": "7 July 2016"}
{"name": "Kristy Lommerse", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just a word of warning for all customers of energy australia they do not like to read your meter leaving you with an expensive bill.</p>", "timestamp": "3 July 2016"}
