{"name": "Dave Healey", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi there. I received a letter from Energy Australia today advising me of a tariff increase effective 1st of July. After entering into a supply contract with Energy Australia some years ago and currently holding my current energy supply contract with you I'm left wondering why I haven't received the contracted notice period notification of the coming tariff increases? Clause 11.2 (c) refers.... In short Energy Australia is contracted to give (at least) one billing period of notice of ANY tariff increase. The last time I looked a billing period is around 90 days....</p>", "timestamp": "28 June 2016"}
{"name": "Kim Warmington", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I do direct debit fortnightly payments for my electricity and I just received a letter that saying in about a month's time Energy Australia will take their first payment of $X. My question is, this amount is $15 more per fortnight than I'm currently paying, but I was never told that the amount I pay currently wasn't covering my usage. That's what I'm assuming given this letter, but it doesn't actually explain it or tell me what's owing on my account to date and why this new figure has been decided upon.</p>", "timestamp": "28 June 2016"}
