{"name": "David James", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just like to know why you deleted my comment that pointed out how Energy Australia was increasing its rates higher than any other retailer? There are many complaints about the same subject on this page - Why did you DELETE mine and not have the decency to respond?</p>", "timestamp": "22 June 2016"}
{"name": "YK Luong", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi EnergyAustralia, I would be very interested to know how my gas bill is calculated as it has suddenly doubled this quarter from roughly $200 to $400. My household has not changed in size, lifestyle and waist lines have remained the same. I spoke to customer service and she told me, that it is an estimate based on average usage which is not a very good explanation. So looking at the graph, my usage has been very consistent in the previous quarters and then in May you have de<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">cided that I have cooked more than 2 times as much. I am very disturbed with this estimate as it certainly does not even remotely comes close to what you would call an average. Even if you used a line of best fit it does not justify this spike! If it is human error then I wouldn't mind as much but if it is a system generated number then I have no confidence in your billing system.</span></p>", "timestamp": "22 June 2016"}
{"name": "Constance Kaporis", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Thank you for notifying me today at short notice that you will be increasing the cost of supplying electricity to my home by over 15%. Because of this, I am no longer a client of energy Australia and have found a better deal elsewhere with cheaper tariffs for power and gas and substantial pay on time discounts. Cheers!</p>", "timestamp": "22 June 2016"}
{"name": "Madhushani H Kirinde", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I received a letter from your debt collectors for an account and for a time period that I haven't even been using and aware of. This is 5 years back and I never lived there for the usage period you are claiming for. Had a very disappointing explanation from your team and I am quite disappointed. I have been with energy Australia for more than 6 years and today I will cancel all my accounts and go to supplier. This is purely because I think you have been unfair and your have your debt management sucks! I will never recommend you to anyone. <br> Thank you</p>", "timestamp": "21 June 2016"}
{"name": "Matthew John Plummer", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/matthew.j.plummer.5?hc_ref=ARSiK_7uBdxaa00Xro2PfxxCkbb6wkhaRHttyC6uPFa0PvfxD0XA28cwzPrk3wadlD0&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>What a way to start the day...price hike is very abrupt and short notice...not very happy at all! I was put onto this company due to your great rates but now it is all blown out! I will be doung something about this, with a commercial property as my home and work combined I have nade a poor choice to join you just a few months ago. Pity there are no laws in place to prevent this extortion!</p>", "timestamp": "21 June 2016"}
{"name": "Jen Bonney", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/jen.hale.395?hc_ref=ARQWroozOxgJj9_QmMdd3qFqTzWFL3bB0Y4NIIYIzj0gruJQx4WnLi8F9c91O5eabrA&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I want to make a complaint... I'm sick of calling and trying to sort out my electricity and gas that was YOUR stuff up!<br> You have charged us under the wrong lot number since August last year and apparently trying to sort it out means hours worth of phone calls!<br> Who do i speak to.... To one get it sorted and 2 make a complaint! I AM SO OVER IT!</p>", "timestamp": "21 June 2016"}
{"name": "Charmaine Higgins", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Be aware that if you are on a plan with Energy Australia. They just bumped up my monthly payment up by $72. Apparently they mailed me a letter even though all my other correspondence comes via email! So dodgy. I opened the plan in July 2015 for $120 per month. It was increased on Feb 2016 to $156 and now in June its been increased to $228.well over what my monthly bills are. That's an increase of $108 per month in 12 months.</p>", "timestamp": "16 June 2016"}
{"name": "Melissa Bannon", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I'm disgusted in this company! I'm sick of being told by your employees that it's my fault why I haven't received bills!! And no one can explain to me why my direct debit was canalled and why you won't reconcet my gas.</p>", "timestamp": "15 June 2016"}
{"name": "Michael Wheeler", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy  Australia failed to send me a bill last quarter. I had to chase them to find out why I hadn't received a bill. I was told last Wednesday that i would have a bill by Monday. Guess what no bill! So I ring Customer (no)Service and again get the run around and I'm told it will be a week until I get my bill.  As I'm due to receive a reading for this quarter I will now have to bills to pay within a week of each other through no fault of my own.     After finding no real sat<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">isfaction with Customer Service I was put through to a rude Manager who although they apoligised still expected all bills be paid on time.  Again 15 minutes of run around with no answers and a case of yeah we know we are in the wrong but tough we won't do anything for you.   I asked so if I didn't ring how long until the mistake was caught 5,6,7, ,8 months?  The answer \" No we would have caught it\". When?  and when you do you slug customers with a huge bill because your systems failed!  Very poor customer service on your behalf ENERGY AUSTRALIA.  When said to the Manager that maybe I should look for another provider, her answer \"That's your prerogative\".  Yes you are correct Ms Manger and since that is your attitude towards  a Customer when you are at fault and treat me rudely I will exercise that prerogative and find a supplier that treats me with the dignity and respect that all customers deserve. Massive Fail Energy Australia</span></p>", "timestamp": "15 June 2016"}
{"name": "Karen Foster", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>So, we've had a dog/s at our home for probably 20 years and now you tell us that if we have:  *a dog  * a gate or * YOUR meter is inside our property your representative <a class=\"_58cn\" href=\"/hashtag/jemena?source=feed_text\" data-ft='{\"type\":104,\"tn\":\"*N\"}'><span class=\"_5afx\"><span aria-label=\"hashtag\" class=\"_58cl _5afz\">#</span><span class=\"_58cm\">Jemena</span></span></a> will no longer leave self-read cards.  So basically, from now on I have no way of having you read THE meter unless we make an appointment and take a day off work to allow access.  Seriously lacking!  Solar and other alternatives look better and better every day <span class=\"_39_n profileLink\">Karen Foster</span></p>", "timestamp": "14 June 2016"}
{"name": "Debs Majumdar", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hey <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=mentions\">EnergyAustralia</a> really tired of your automated caller telling me in an inaudible tone, to call another number for me to wait on hold to speak to someone about something in which I have no idea what the subject was about. If it's something urgent - please ask one of your operators to call me directly - no doubt you have my number already. Thanks</p>", "timestamp": "14 June 2016"}
