{"name": "Chantelle Hernandez-Butterworth", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/chantelle.hernandezbutterworth?hc_ref=ARTlDjjebRyc0k5aG788FqlZnVBsHXcW7kV4p9lP341zPupu_5MpAm_W3zi4ImRO0ac&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi, we have a big issue with you guys. We lived in a two bedroom unit, we had you as our energy provider. In the three months we lived there, we received one bill for over $1000.00 which according to your graphs is more than an 8 person household. Given that we had a fridge with four star energy rating, no clothes dryer, no aircon, we had a microwave and toaster. No t.v, if we ran more than three appliances it would trip the circuit. My partner and I worked full time so appli<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ances where turned off at the switch. We cannot see how it's possible to have used that much electricity in the 90 days we where there for. Have disputed the charges and had, had no word back despite knowing you have our new address, instead you have sent through our bill to debt collectors. Can you please give us an explanation as to why you have not worked this through? We have asked for a summary of our usage and had not heard back.</span></p>", "timestamp": "3 June 2016"}
