{"name": "Jonathan Doig", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/jondoig?hc_ref=ARQPJfJcXlAqS5CsFJa68b2J_Hfdvi4nMZejEfaOaCvNcvc0iOKhxml6X6B_1yClTgw", "comment": "<p>A little feedback from this ex-customer</p>", "timestamp": "2 June 2016"}
{"name": "Stephen McNamara", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/stephen.mcnamara.98?hc_ref=ARQ-TVG31tG7YW4JViCRtcF1FztdeaALGXGSa3RGl5EOT0V9mTBD_0eFjVr0Kakkgr4&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Will never use this company again around a year ago my hot water system gave up so got a quote for continuos hot water anyway it was installed then they bill me exactly what was quoted. Charging me for a wall which is already thier as one example. I rang them and asked them to review the price closs to a year later they send me the same bill for 5609.89 minus a discount of 100 and a further emergency response discount of 250 now asking me to pay 4744.60 my problem is what thier charging for and as they don't want to be fair and charge for what is used i will be going to fairtrading and making this as public as i can.</p>", "timestamp": "1 June 2016"}
{"name": "Simon Doss", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/simon.isaac.731?hc_ref=ARQhnnGPuir6Ux6ysV9KnN2jXDJx32QAMGlMU8axvek0lL-Zx9ijTzuO4Eys_VCgEVw&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>To whom it may concern,</p>", "timestamp": "1 June 2016"}
{"name": "Julia Truong", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/julia.truong.735?hc_ref=ARTSax4r_MlUxB5-91PwQ_jBJgUusFDsvLlissqndMYjUE2evVCSkib5MPYi0SGUdZk&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Extremely disappointed with EnergyAustralia. We are currently left powerless in our home in Victoria. This is the second time our electricity was cut off in less than two months since we've moved into this property. EnergyAustralia promised to connect us with electricity, to then realise that it was never done properly when it was cut the first time. We thought it was fixed last month, but we've discovered its still not completed as we're powerless again. EnergyAustralia staff was refusing to help as our conversation clocked over 6.30pm and it was time to clock off. We were transferred to other companies. <br> We're still powerless now.</p>", "timestamp": "30 May 2016"}
{"name": "Kim McGuire", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/kim.mcguire.967?hc_ref=ARTaqV0jjABIAEkHiQ8c7_tdWOj9IETVeFM1ny8No_Meno_CLyIYa73IwWW2_7XceVE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This does not seem right...<br> My husband, Peter was listed as the primary account holder - .  I am also listed on the account so that I could deal with enquiries - Peter had been suffering from Lung Cancer for the past 3 years.  I called today to notify Energy Australia that Peter died 17.5.16 and that I the account should be transferred into my name.<br> This is when I was told that I would need to pay for a NEW CONNECTION.  This is not a situation that calls for a new connection. My name is on the account, I have been fully or partially responsible for the account for 33 years. I am gobsmacked.</p>", "timestamp": "29 May 2016"}
{"name": "Anna Perriam", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi guys. Just wanting to know why someone's slacking off and my bills are coming extremely late? When I first signed up you were fairly good, now I'm constantly chasing you guys for my bills.. I try do the best I can by paying money towards my bills every fortnight but this is getting a bit silly.. Someone came to read my meter just before I left for holidays either the 20-21, surely doesn't take two weeks to generate the bill or at least get it online..</p>", "timestamp": "28 May 2016"}
{"name": "Jacqui Broekhof", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>worst energy company ever. my bill trippled when i went with them. the meter was faulty and when I contacted the energy ombudsman, they asked EA to check it, but they didn't bother ... this went on for months until i moved out.... they never checked it. 2 years later a collections service calls.</p>", "timestamp": "27 May 2016"}
{"name": "Lilea Sward", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>What a waste of time.  I did think that I would change my oven and get a gas cooktop and utilise the gas, or use the gas bayonet for a heater, so I connected.  Silly me. I have now disconnected.  Of course the reading can't be done until 1.06.2016. I understand that.  What I don't understand is not having a reminder account for a bill that was apparently owing for my previous address (which I left the beginning of December). So, trying to disconnect I am informed of the bill <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">still owing. Also, all the notes have to go in of how antsy I have now become since I have to stay on the line whilst the notes go in because otherwise he can't make the notes. The time he is paid for whilst I stay online talking to him rather than being forwarded to the sales staff that will disconnect my service, is much more important.  I realise I WAS only a customer. My time is so much more expendable and worth so little in the scheme of things so that I am spending more in wasting my time than the worth of the bill for which I do not have a reminder.  Amazingly, both my addresses have the same mailing address so I am a little confused.</span></p>", "timestamp": "26 May 2016"}
