{"name": "Maureen Carson", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>This is one of the worst Energy companies on this earth.<br> I moved into my unit in February 16<br> Trying to get my power sorted is like removing teeth from a chook, I  moved into a unit and connecting to my name was not a problem the problem is that when they come to read the metre we have the problem.</p>", "timestamp": "18 May 2016"}
{"name": "Claire Harris", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/claire.obst?hc_ref=ARTa9tvdo7GIwW2znivkLHP1r-9oJf_x-K6nY2ZroeYf9mSyzKy0kIjmjUb-7JM9ebs&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I cant believe that out 'account' has been open since september last year and we still havent received a bill.... i have phoned about it 4 times, each time given the exact same run around, then told i need to be transferred to some<br> mystical 'other department' that magically always has a phone problem which means i cant get through. then a truly lovely person (for real, i think they hire nice people to gloss over their overall incompetence) always promises to call me back with<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> answers, and they call me back to say no answers but they will get a meter read and send the bill, and then they never call again. then we don't get a bill, and i have to do it all again... this is absolutely the WORST and most unprofessional company i've ever dealt with. Today i'll gove them one more chance to find answers, and they better be crediting the massive bill when it comes. I am definitely gonna need to call the ombusman this time.... DO NOT USE GO WITH ENERGY AUSTRALIA!!!!</span></p>", "timestamp": "18 May 2016"}
{"name": "Sarah Smith", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I'm seriously sick of dealing with incompetent accounts and your company and wasting my time to call you to sort the problem that supposedly has been sorted numerous times.<br> I warned you I receive one more disconnection letter or phone call or text I'm changing supplier.<br> When I get my day off tomorrow my account is being transferred to someone that can read notes and follow clear instructions<br> As a loyal customer for over 15 years I've had enough <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "17 May 2016"}
{"name": "Marty Bailey", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Alright, I have been trying to get an electricity account put in my name through you guys since December of 2015. Every time I call or go online to register, I am told my account has been set up and I will be receiving a welcome pack, to only find a disconnect warning letter every few weeks later in my mailbox. The first two times I put it down to mistakes or miscommunication, perhaps a poorly designed website, but after three more attempts now taking up plenty of my own time to try and get this sorted, I've decided if you want your money, you can contact me. At this rate, I shouldn't have to pay for anything thus far as I have taken the initiative to contact you on five separate occasions to be told there is no account registered in my name or at my address, but that you will set one up. I have bigger things to worry about. Sort it out.</p>", "timestamp": "17 May 2016"}
