{"name": "Rob Tupanceski", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Very disappointed with the level of service (or lack there of) at Energy Australia. It appears that due to lack of communication and administration I was informed my electricity would be cut (despite having paid all my bills on time) because they failed to adequately complete the transfer of my details from a competing company. After learning I was being billed for the wrong meter and following a number of lengthy discussions with your Customer Services representatives, I was<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> assured my electricity would NOT be disconnected.  This proved false as I came home from work to find no power in my place; followed by an hour conversation with the emergency department, I was told that the earliest my electricity could be reconnected was the next day. To add fuel to the fire, I was also informed that somebody would need to be home when the technician showed up \u2013 at no mention of time of day, or I would again not have power for ANOTHER day.</span></p>", "timestamp": "12 May 2016"}
