{"name": "Sandra Rechichi", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Daughter and son-in-law have just recently moved into their home and on Monday, the gas cut off through no fault of their own. Apparently clerical errors in the transfer of paperwork between Energy Australia and AGL( billing company of previous owner). Yet, 2 days later, still no hot water and no gas for cooking. This in not looking after new customers, despite the \"sympathetic\" tones of the call centre operators.</p>", "timestamp": "10 May 2016"}
{"name": "Greg Alexander", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/greg.alexander.1481?hc_ref=ARSyNVr0qQUK4T2xbTxkSFPZVImZ8QnRCtPmWZt3JLZFuNrjwZuQEcJOIKjf3ZzQuYc&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>18 months of errors in bills, a replacement metre with no explanation as to what the error had been and whether we'd been overcharged. Forgetting we were on \"hold\" while this was sorted out and being sent reminders. A new metre fix when we complained again. My request for a written summary of what happened. And all I got was all these bills at once undoing the past and then redoing it. </p>", "timestamp": "10 May 2016"}
{"name": "Matt Salter", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Our electricity was wrongly disconnected on Wednesday due to a request to do so from Energy Australia. When contacted, Energy Australia could provide no reason for the disconnection. We were promised that the gas would be restored by midnight Thursday; it wasn't. Then promised it would be restored by midnight Friday; it wasn't. Now the weekend, the customer service centre is closed and we're facing a weekend without gas. We can't cook, we can't bath our one year old. Would someone please contact us ASAP and arrange to have the gas reconnected immediately?</p>", "timestamp": "6 May 2016"}
{"name": "Sean Cee", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Recently, I called your call centre. I was concerned that my electric usage as very high, as I live alone, every appliance I use, including all lighting, is the most energy efficient on the market, yet my usage was between 1000-1300kwh/quarter, similar to what a large house with multiple tenants would use.<br> I requested a meter test - and your call centre operator tried to talk me out of it, saying \"if the meter was faulty, your usage would be up and down, not consistently high<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">\". <br> Not only was did this statement make no sense, it's inappropriate for such a person to make an assumption of what a test may or may not find. They are a call centre operator, not a qualified technician.<br> I had the meter tested. It was faulty. It was replaced. On My bill I've just received, the old (faulty) meter registered 622kwh in 48 days. The new meter registered 216kwh in 47 days. Almost 1/3.<br> Bottom line is - if your usage is higher than it should be - get your meter checked. Worst case - you have to pay the $150 meter test - best case, it's free, and your bills will halve.</span></p>", "timestamp": "6 May 2016"}
{"name": "Patricia Newton", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Has anyone else out there had a problem with Energy Australia? We are being fraudulently billed for a gas account an address in Victoria since April 2015 and no one will take initiative to help us get this resolved. It's with police, Victoria Ombudsman and yet Energy Australia still fail to resolve this matter. We don't even hold any other accounts with Energy Australia!! </p>", "timestamp": "6 May 2016"}
{"name": "Tahlia Scarborough", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/people/Tahlia-Scarborough/100011249923923?hc_ref=ARQzJhx4LnpQpeB2NRhZu2_ktWYBFLs_TMzbHYBDWiZuIcXQ06F3P5XwFOEESVL1zgE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Pathetic excuse of a \"team\" or a \"wise call\" <br> I've moved into a new property over a week ago.<br> Monday when electricity was supposed to be connected, no one connected it. <br> I called, called the distributer. They told me to wait! I waited all day and night in the dark with my 2yo as you said it would be between 9am and midnight. Tuesday I had to call up and work my way through consultant to consultant to find out what happened... Ended up having to break into the power box outsid<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">e and flick the switch myself. Like why didn't anyone tell me they were at my house connecting my electricity!<br> Thursday comes around, \"Gas is supposed to be connected today!\" A meter installation... NOTHING ONCE AGAIN. 5 long bloody phone calls today &amp; not one consultant called me back! You guys need to take a look about what you pride yourself on. Gaining customers or helping customers? <br> Last Friday is when I organised all of this, and you still cant tell me what's going on!!! How am I supposed to trust my son &amp; I in this service??? Pathetic! <br> Now I have to wait till Monday for hot water??? I organised all of this 10 days ago! <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span></span></p>", "timestamp": "6 May 2016"}
