{"name": "Sayam Seigell", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Dear Energy Australia, with all the money you make and take from customers I find it hard to believe you invest what seems to me to be like 2 cents in your systems and computers.Every month I am having to take 30 minutes off my day to call you repeatedly with the same issue of wrong bill payments due date and you somehow AGAIN manage to do the same thing! Firstly you send me a bill worth $643 approx. 6-8 months after I vacate my premises citing bill reading errors at your end<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> which by the way I find very hard to trust the authenticity of NOW, then you give me an extension to pay it till may 2016 and then you keep sending me letters with a due date to pay NOW or you take legal action? When i call your call center they keep reassuring my my extension date stands true but yet somehow this is not the case with your reminder letters? So either your computers are old and too tired now to spit out right dates or somehow magically the payment due dates keep getting changed by elves! Not only do I question the authenticity of your meter reading now, I don't trust any reassurances I get from your call center staff regarding extension dates given the letters i receive from you are hostile! So now I am forced to make this 'public' hoping there will be a HUMAN out there to help me out!</span></p>", "timestamp": "7 April 2016"}
{"name": "EnergyAustralia", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?hc_ref=ARS-w-mSnJAV6UK0CQJoY9zwt34kv7L6IBhrdvIuqrY84Ar4zzSAbsKo25vGQ1MScW8", "comment": "<p>Here's some realistic ways to reduce your power bills <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=mentions\">EnergyAustralia</a></p>", "timestamp": "7 April 2016"}
{"name": "Chris Parsons", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Can I just say your customer service is quite poor. We got stuffed around with no gas bills for near on a year. Then doubled billed (2 accounts for the one property?!) for at least a year. Then without any notification to confirm, cancel one account. Then 6 months later, transfer credit from cancelled account to active account. Paid $200 off about 3 weeks ago. Now have the hide to disconnect the same day I receive a disconnection warning because of $175 in arrears. All this b<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ecause I HAD NO IDEA WHERE MY ACCOUNT WAS UPTO. Just spent the best part of an hour on the phone. Where one girl was very helpful and said it shouldn't be a problem to arrange something in terms of payment and reconnect. But then your payments and connections team refuse to assist me even after explaining (3 times) what went on. Pathetic. I will not be connecting with you guys ever again. And I will advise many others to do the same. Thanks for your service. Or lack thereof.<br> -very annoyed customer</span></p>", "timestamp": "7 April 2016"}
{"name": "Ash Block", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>You would have to been the worst company ever to deal with, installed an aircon in my house. We made a complaint. After further discussions and complaints someone finally came out, then I kept getting threats for debt collectors and court cases for not paying for install. So as I pay for install I never hear anything else from your incompetent company. How convenient... </p>", "timestamp": "7 April 2016"}
{"name": "Luke Slingsby", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Absolute pathetic. Ongoing dispute since January 2012. Partner and I disconnected gas an electricity at the same time. However Energy Australia only managed to disconnect the Gas account. However when another person tried to connect the electricity they want to bill me for the full period from  20 November to 23 January when we moved out 7th December. There amazing solution is to just do an average cost per day. Totally not right as the property did not have a smart meter and<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> this is a massive assumption. Pathetic. Also to not I have been hung up on 3 times, promised returned phone calls which never occur and the icing on the cake department manager Cherrylyn informed me that the account would receive a zero balance and I would be called back. Yet another failing on this pathetic excuse for a company. I would encourage all people to avoid them.</span></p>", "timestamp": "6 April 2016"}
{"name": "Joshua Daniel Evans", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>You should change your name from Energy Australia to Energy Rude with the way your managers and staff carry on. you lot are the most Un-Australian company. Instead of just waving a $16 charge on a bill that was generated because of the landlord on a property we rented (this was generated well after we had left) we are getting billed. Your staff were rude &amp; abusive to my wife so we are taking this to the ombudsman as we refuse to bend over &amp; pay for something that was not from our usage. </p>", "timestamp": "6 April 2016"}
{"name": "Nilanjan Nag", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/nilanjanbirati?hc_ref=ARQ2S5AXA3ej2S-yb5VjfqOZCRHVpgHnzjUPMoFpl2YPZrAjoaqWSvVovFvoRHiLmYE&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi,<br> I have applied for a new electricity connection account number 7357525278. First appointment for connection was on friday but no body came in.When I called your customer care its was told me that new booking has been made with priority and it will done on saturday. Today when I called Energx they said they said they have no booking from Energy Australia for my unit.This is very frustrating and horrible service..ultimate harrasment for me.Even before getting your connectio<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">n I am getting service like ,Don't know what will happen after.<br> I expect that this will be sorted out ASAP and I don't need to stay in Dark anymore..</span></p>", "timestamp": "1 April 2016"}
{"name": "Sarah Heath", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I've lost power in Beachmere. Doesn't seem to be fixable on the switch board...</p>", "timestamp": "31 March 2016"}
{"name": "Geoff Guymer", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/geoff.guymer.9?hc_ref=ARQaZjKXwmU08vnuyqQGmbt5cbG-OEWJcmD1klVDMSmwOubROuqRw9wnsCoNKB0sVuI&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Where to start? Part of my package of benefits to move my three services to this ramshackle organisation included two vouchers for free service or repair by Energy Australia. I made a call 2 weeks ago due to an emergency with water leaking from rooftop air con. Lots of water. I was told that I had to talk to home services and they are 'sort of' a different entity, it's really nothing to do with Energy Aust. Well I have a letter confirming that I have these benefits for min 12<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> months from Michelle Monoghan, General Manager, Energy Australia. <br> I have called 4 times and been promised callbacks 3 times, I have asked to make official complaints to Energy Aust. I get transferred to diff depts, disconnected, told that I cannot speak to supervisors, asked to repeat myself every time, emailed, put on hold for hours, and still I am no closer to a solution.<br> Through my calculation this is costing me $20 per day in wasted water. <br> I am going to call the Energy Ombudsman, I am going to call a local plumber to do the repair, I am going to insist on compensation for cost of water, plumber and my wasted time, and I expect a call from Michelle Monaghan.<br> Energy Australia needs to get their act together and get the right hand talking to the left hand.<br> This is far from satisfactory and far from over!</span></p>", "timestamp": "31 March 2016"}
{"name": "Sharnie L Monkley", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/sharniel.monkley?hc_ref=ARSInsPflU4jWT3_li-NQ2N3GhDOMnOM3QnZN19ykMbkWxhtM6R-ZA5zUKXN7yuQucM&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Thank you very much to the loverly lady that helped me today some positive feed back!!! We v been going through a really tough time and she was really loverly helping us work out a payment an and giving us a bigger discount then we had! So very helpful and loverly!</p>", "timestamp": "31 March 2016"}
{"name": "Lisa Ingram", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/lisa.ingram.397?hc_ref=ARSAlEY9Sxi05QKrA7tgfORKsiepKL7gLfZu7ENo4BrWdSREko0x1wdgB7vRruMaUXg&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I was without power for an entire weekend because energy Australia isn't open over the weekend. I called all weekend and no one could help me until Monday. I lost $200 of food, had to inconvenience friends because I couldnt stay at my own house over night. On top of this, Energy Australia is only open 9am-5pm on weekdays so I had to leave work early so I could be at home and on the phone to Energy Australia. That's a few hours I need to be compensated for leaving work early. <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">On top of all of this, I was told the my power would take 4 hours to turn on, leaving me at home on a Monday night without power - AGAIN. All up, I was inconvenienced from Saturday morning until Monday night 10pm. This is simply unacceptable that a huge company like this doesnt have support over the weekend. It is completely impracticle for a company of this size to only have phone support between 9am-5pm on week days. Very unhappy customer.</span></p>", "timestamp": "31 March 2016"}
{"name": "Molly Green", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/himollygreen?hc_ref=ARTvs1LJAUGbUUojZCi3LwXLkmNJxGLiYU4y9ZsLGXTPk5I2iOrOvbgMEFZLP3f_NBg&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I organised connection at my new address two weeks ago. Move in, no power. Three phone calls and 1.5 hours of my day wasted it's now 8pm and here I am sitting in the dark with all my food in the freezer defrosting. Not good enough.</p>", "timestamp": "31 March 2016"}
{"name": "Samantha Jackson", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>What a joke!! <br> For the second time this week Energy Australia!<br> Waited at home all day for our initial meter reading to be read. <br> I call up at 3pm just to make sure someone is still coming and NOPE!! <br> We advise that the consultant did not process the request correctly. <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"><br> Not very good customer service. <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f8d/1/16/1f621.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83d\ude21</span></span><br> Sorry we will have to rebook AGAIN!</span></p>", "timestamp": "30 March 2016"}
{"name": "Pearl Wilmen", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Good evening <br> I'm in Barnsey NSW and power went out twenty minutes ago, any idea why and when it will be back on?<br> Thanks</p>", "timestamp": "26 March 2016"}
{"name": "EnergyAustralia", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?hc_ref=ARRTx52SthNrLmDEY4jCuNnYC3yTddIHrK2RhUsM8-8peVhFZXr3BxJ_7GBgsTcmbzw", "comment": "<p>I would like to thank one of my favourite barbers, <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/barbersdream?fref=mentions\">Jordon Mckenny</a>, for supporting my business. </p>", "timestamp": "25 March 2016"}
{"name": "N/A", "link": "N/A", "comment": "<p>I would like to thank one of my favourite barbers, <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/barbersdream?fref=mentions\">Jordon Mckenny</a>, for supporting my business. </p>", "timestamp": "25 March 2016"}
{"name": "Rebecca McIntosh", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/rebecca.hall.522?hc_ref=ARR4mS1A7ESuanX7NolqORiq8kWXxRNOoa9T5QZLKHlCDWeKn9hu3BaoLQRmdoCJGA8&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Very disappointed with Energy Australia and its lack of out of hours customer service.  I had arranged with you for electricry connection at our new residense for yesterday and to my absolute disappointment, no power. I could not contact anyone at Energy Australia for an explanation. I contacted powerecor and they were able to advise that the connection failed yesterday morning due to the mains not being switched off.  Firstly, I was not made aware of this, secondly why wasn't I informed yesterday when this failure occurred in the morning.  I now have no power for the entire long weekend because I cannot arrange for Energy Australia to resubmit another connection request... this sucks!!.  I am contacting AGL first thing and switching as they firstly, have out of hours service and secondly, guarantee their connections.</p>", "timestamp": "25 March 2016"}
{"name": "Ames N Ruby", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi to Kim Clarke - Chief Customer Officer..</p>", "timestamp": "25 March 2016"}
{"name": "Tamarra Love", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hello, I am trying to get in touch via a complaints/feedback form, however, even though it says you can on your website, the links simply do not work. I would like a situation rectified on our account as soon as possible. Both my husband and I have called, lodged our concession card online etc. And yet still, even though we were told the bill would be recalculated this has not happened. Please can someone contact me with regards to this.</p>", "timestamp": "24 March 2016"}
{"name": "Darren Agius", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Just wanted to give you a little feedback on my latest interaction with your company. I receive a letter saying that my gas meter will be replaced as a part of general upkeep or something, I had no issues with my meter at all.<br> A couple of weeks later we get a knock at the door, my partner answers it to a unkempt man who simply says I just changed your gas meter I need to come inside to relight your appliances.<br> No offering of of any identity , no politeness. My partner of cour<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">se refused him entry, and he left.<br> I get home from work and am told what had happened and that i needed to relight the appliances, I go to the ducted gas heater and it is clicking away trying to relight itself, for god knows how long. this was the ONLY appliance I could relight, the hot water service wouldn't relight and the oven wouldn't work.<br> I call your company and after explaining the situation am told someone will call me as i need to give them access to the property.This could take up to 48 hrs!!!! ridiculous.<br> The next morning , without a phone call again, someone turns up.<br> Luckily my son was home to let him in, this man then proceeded to  break my plants accessing the hot water service, lit it and left, not sorting out the oven not lighting. If I was contacted as I was told was going to happen, I would have cleared easier access for him and the plants would not have been broken.<br> I then have to ring your company back, speak to 4 different people again, and once again am told \" this is not an emergency, we'll have someone out as soon as we can, but this happens when we do meter changes, sometimes appliances just dont restart, and you'll have to get a plumber to fix them. Not a very helpful response, if you didn't replace a meter that was working fine , nothing would be broken, everything would be working fine as it was ,I could have cooked my dinner last night and I could have had a shower this morning.<br> Overall I'm very disappointed in the professionalism of all of this from start to finish. Especially the lack of identity and follow up from your company.<br> I await your response<br> Darren Agius</span></p>", "timestamp": "23 March 2016"}
{"name": "Andrea Mason", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I don't usually go out of my way to write or even like a page but I reckon Energy Australia is one of the best Electricity providers I have ever been with and yes I have been with a few. There staff are so friendly and helpful and efficient. One time I was dreading my quarterly bill thinking it was going to hit the thousands being a very hot summer, having the pool pump and air conditioning constantly on having 2 little kiddies around the house.  Was shocked to see how cheap it was. Big thumbs up Energy Australia <span class=\"_47e3 _5mfr\" title=\"grin emoticon\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f51/1/16/1f603.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"_7oe\">:-D</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "22 March 2016"}
{"name": "Grace Wight", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/grace.wight?hc_ref=ARRoZLEiqkRJNIodXAGWcbmaCYRGM_tUmJbQljpp49eawA1n18NYk6hFR42RIvw7Zig&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>It seems my post has been deleted. Was hoping to email Dani if I can be sent her email address ASAP that would be great.</p>", "timestamp": "22 March 2016"}
{"name": "Craig Martin", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/gmhuc?hc_ref=ARTNyJ8aD6v3MKG81W94SsJhe40M4F7ZPhTDWZ-APBUzboznuWPH4kPADGoBizPdxMs&fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Why do you not have an after hours service to call when you've gone and disconnected someone's power while they're in hospital for 2 weeks getting multiple surgeries and my wife and 2 yo son have to find out when they walk in the door at 8 30 at night. </p>", "timestamp": "22 March 2016"}
