{"name": "Phil Hiosan", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I just got a final bill advising me my account is in credit. The letter also advises I need to provide my postal address for the refund cheque - how do you reckon I got your letter!!!! and you wonder why I went elsewhere Energy Australia.</p>", "timestamp": "22 March 2016"}
{"name": "Jack Saynor", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi EnergyAustralia<br> Last January I was offered new rates as my current ones had expired. After some discussion with your company reps because I was not happy, we reached a compromise &amp; I agreed to new rates. I have just received my latest bill only to find the new rates we agreed on have not been applied. The rates used are the ones which were offered to me in January that I wouldn't accept. I wasted a lot of time in January/February negotiating new rates with you. Am I now again going to have to waste more time sorting out your mistake that should not have occurred?<br> Jack Saynor.</p>", "timestamp": "21 March 2016"}
{"name": "Tan Tanz", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>I think your phone line is down! Can't get through. The call fails. Doesn't even ring just fails! <span class=\"_5mfr _47e3\"><img class=\"img\" height=\"16\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/f34/1/16/1f914.png\" width=\"16\" alt=\"\"><span class=\"_7oe\">\ud83e\udd14</span></span></p>", "timestamp": "21 March 2016"}
{"name": "Nick Pearson", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Why do you send out a paper bill when I've got an automatic transfer set up? It means three weeks after I pay my electricity bill, you deduct the same amount from my account? I want my money back.</p>", "timestamp": "21 March 2016"}
{"name": "Jimmy Ng", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Hi, I paid my electricity bill well before the due date. Literally the day after I received the e-statement. The due date was 15th of March. I paid it on the 26th of Feb and I received the statement on the 25th of Feb.</p>", "timestamp": "21 March 2016"}
{"name": "Tracy Bezzant", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>MASSIVE COMPLAINT... someone needs to PM me as I am just about to close both my accounts with you after 4 years! Bad customer service, always getting bills wrong! sending wrong bills to different address, cancelling bills? I moved cities and still bad service...</p>", "timestamp": "16 March 2016"}
{"name": "Justin Lucas", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Absolutely wowful service.<br> Yesterday I decided I would give this company a go an an switch over to your service, once I have done this i have orgainsed for electricity to be connected on Wednesday the 16th of march between 8am an 1pm. I decided to ring up this  morning to confirm an nothing has be locked in for this. So i then changed the time from 11am to 4pm an re done the whole proccess. Ince again nothing has be locked in. So i have missed out on a full day of work with no electricity been yet connected. <br> What are you going to do to resolve this problem from your incompetented phone operators!</p>", "timestamp": "15 March 2016"}
{"name": "Clare Lollback", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Energy Australia, I rent in Caulfield South and the power is off till 1500hrs. I spoke to my neighbours and nobody received any notification of power line works/outages for today. It's 31c with no fans or air conditioning. Not good enough.</p>", "timestamp": "15 March 2016"}
{"name": "Sean Cee", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Rang EA to get a meter test. I SPECIFICALLY asked whether the tech will need access to the main switch. Your call centre operator said, no just the meter. Later told by sa power networks, that yes, they will need access to the main switch. This is quite important, as it's the difference between me going to work, or having to stay home to provide access. </p>", "timestamp": "15 March 2016"}
