{"name": "Evie Leslie", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Started an electricity reconnection on the 10 Feb. have made several calls, have made several trips to arrange access (this is a rental property and we live 30 mins away) and have been told repeatedly the technician will phone us on 3 occasions prior to arriving. Have not had one single call and still awaiting connection 6 days later, after repeated arrangements have not occurred. Each time we ring have to start the whole process AGAIN. Have been told twice the electricity is on and it is NOT. Why the constant lies and inefficiency? Have never had such hopeless service (?), if you can call it that. Lift your game Energy Australia, not good enough.</p>", "timestamp": "16 February 2016"}
{"name": "Terry Gartland", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>Moved into my house Friday 12th Febuary having arranged electric and gas through Energy Australia. When I arrived at 9am electric was on, great. Tried gas without any success. Rang Energy Australia regarding gas issue and was passed around department to department then when somebody did speak to me he was foreign and couldn't understand me. Through broken English we managed to have some correspondence where the gentleman informed me the supply had been plugged and would take <span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">48 hrs business days to just request any action. This means no hot water, stove or heating. Today is Tuesday 16th, awoke again to no gas, rang Energy Australia again to enquire what was going on with my situation. The gentleman told me a technician had been and the line wasn't plugged, I sad still no supply in my house so he arranged another technician to come today or tomorrow. Still not done today so best case scenario is tomorrow Wednesday 17th. I have children here and we will have had no hot water, stove or heating for 6 days with no guarantee the problem will be resolved tomorrow !!!!!  Do you think this is fair or appropriate service???  I can tell you as soon as (if) the gas is connected properly I will be changing suppliers and will be seeking further advice as to what I can do regarding the inconvenience your company has caused me.</span></p>", "timestamp": "15 February 2016"}
