{"name": "Stephanie McManus", "link": "https://www.facebook.com/EnergyAustralia/?fref=nf", "comment": "<p>On Monday 18 January 2016 I received notification that my request to transfer my electricity and gas from Origin Energy to Energy Australia had been processed.<br> I did not request this and I called Energy Australia to find out what was going on. They apologized for the error and informed me that the request would not be processed. I was also advised that I had over paid an account when I was a customer back in October 2015 and was due a refund cheque. <br> A letter was then sent to<span class=\"text_exposed_hide\">...</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"> me by Energy Australia confirming the refund and asking that I complete the bottom section of the letter confirming my address etc and return for the refund. I have completed all of this and not received my refund.<br> On Tuesday 9 February 2016 I received a text message from Energy Australia advising me that my new account had been created and providing me with an account number 6677834158.<br> I called Energy Australia again to advise that I did not request this and the woman I spoke with was very rude and condescending stating that obviously I had requested the change and perhaps I forgot the conversation. Clearly I would remember having such a conversation and I can assure you that I have not \u201cforgot\u201d that I signed up with you. This woman proceeded to tell me that an external provider of yours was the one to send through the information to you that I wanted to move. This is an issue in itself as I did not request this however when I told this to your customer service representative, she proceeded to hang up on me.<br> I called back approximately 30 mins later and there was no record of my call on file. I proceeded to explain the situation again and was then told that I had completed an online request on 9 December 2015. On 9 December 2015 I was in Los Angeles and certainly wasn\u2019t completing any online requests with Energy Australia.<br> I have asked to have all my details removed from your system and not to be contacted by Energy Australia again and was advised this is not possible. <br> I understand you have no real interest in helping me as I have no intention of ever being an Energy Australia customer again but I need to understand how this has happened. I am concerned for my privacy and that this can happen. <br> I need to be assured that this won\u2019t happen again. I have informed Origin Energy of the situation and they will be requesting the account back.<br> I would like some kind of resolution and reassurance on this matter. I would also like to know where my refund cheque is as the last person I spoke with couldn\u2019t find any record of any refund.</span></p>", "timestamp": "9 February 2016"}
